title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to sour cream mixture.
Pour half of the batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with half of mixed sugar and cinnamon.
Add remaining butter.
Top with remaining sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: chicken-macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Combine ingredients, adding chicken last.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking for another 15 minutes.

title: texas beans
directions: Brown beef and onion until onion is tender.
Add to pinto beans.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for about 1 hour.

title: layered crab spread
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese, lemon juice, Worcestershire and garlic powder until fluffy.
Stir in onion.
On serving plate, spread cheese mixture into 7-inch circle.
Top with chili sauce, then crab meat.
Cover; chill.
Serve with crackers.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: instant tropical juice
directions: Pour beverages into a glass and enjoy.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: microwave old-fashioned pot roast
directions: Place roast in 3-quart casserole.
In a small bowl, mix tomatoes, onion, garlic powder, cayenne and pepper.
Add cinnamon stick.
Pour over roast. Cover. Microwave on High for 5 minutes. Reduce to Medium-low (150°).
Microwave for 1 hour longer, turning roast over after 1/2 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Re-cover. Microwave on Medium-low for 30 to 45 minutes or until roast and vegetables are tender.
Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: bishop's bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt in a large bowl. Stir in nuts, dates, cherries and chocolate chips.
In a small bowl beat eggs with sugar.
Stir into flour mixture.
Turn into a greased and floured 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until tester comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack.
Bread is best wrapped and stored at least 1 day before slicing and serving.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Place strawberries in bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar; let stand until thawed, then slice.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt and baking soda in large bowl.
Blend oil and eggs into strawberries.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir in pecans, blending until just mixed.
Divide batter between pans.
Bake loaves until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 45 to 50 minutes. Cool before slicing.
These freeze well.

title: pumpkin butter
directions: Wash
pumpkin; cut in half.
Clean the inside.
Put 1/2 of pumpkin on pan.
Cook in oven at 300° for 40 minutes; check with fork
to see if tender.
After pumpkin cools, peel it and mash pumpkin.
Put
1 cup of sugar to 1 cup of pumpkin.
Add 2 tablespoons
of cinnamon and 2 tablespoons allspice; mix well. Place in
oven;
stir once in a while.
(If it starts to boil, cut down
oven
temperature.) When pumpkin butter is thick on spoon, take out of oven.
Put in jars and seal.

title: banana crush
directions: Make syrup of water and sugar by heating until sugar is dissolved.
Combine with remaining ingredients except ginger ale and freeze.
Fill glasses with softened banana freeze to half full.
Fill glasses the rest of the way with ginger ale.

title: muddy buddies
directions: Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine in saucepan or in microwave and stir.
Add vanilla and mix.
Pour over cereal and mix in large bowl.
Put mixture in Ziploc bags with powdered sugar and shake until cereal is covered with sugar.
Spread cereal out on wax paper to dry.
Store in airtight container.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix cottage cheese and jello until jello is dissolved.
Add Cool Whip and drained fruit to cottage cheese and jello mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: pina colada yogurt
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
You can enjoy it right away or refrigerate for about 1 hour.

title: liebesschleifen(love knots)
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add melted butter.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Add rum.
Let stand one hour.

title: blueberry custard
directions: Spread 1 side of bread with butter.
Cut each slice into 4 squares.
Arrange in lightly buttered 8-inch square baking dish, buttered side up.
Sprinkle with blueberries and cinnamon.
Heat milk and sugar until warm (do not boil) and stir until sugar dissolves.
Combine warm milk mixture, eggs and vanilla.
Pour over blueberries.
Set dish in larger pan; add hot water to depth of 1-inch.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except marshmallows, well.
Bake in buttered casserole dish at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Add marshmallows for topping the last few minutes of baking, if desired.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Slowly melt chili in saucepan.
Fix casserole with Fritos, tomatoes and sauce, onions and chili.
Cover with Fritos and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
I like to add cheese.
Serve with salad.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon crisp; mix with onion.
Add to beans and the rest of ingredients.
Pour in casserole dish and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Beat flour, sugar, margarine and salt in large bowl on medium speed until crumbly (mixture will be dry).
Press firmly in pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Prepare filling.

title: chicken or turkey pie
directions: Combine last 7 ingredients and pour into baked pie shell. Cover with 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Top with 1 cup finely crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: frozen choco-mint torte
directions: Mix and pat in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Save a few crumbs for the top.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown ground beef and add taco seasoning. Cube Velveeta.
Add all ingredients in crock-pot.
Ready when cheese has melted and mixture is hot.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together cake mix and jello.
Add oil, strawberries, milk and eggs.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim fat from beef and cut across grain into bite size strips. In small bowl, stir together sour cream, flour and tomato paste. Stir in water, bouillon and pepper.
Set aside.
Cook fettuccine according to package.

title: french onion soup
directions: In Dutch oven or large saucepan, cook onions in butter until golden.
Add water, bouillon, paprika, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Simmer (covered) for 15 to 20 minutes to blend flavors.

title: lasagna toss
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef with onions and garlic; drain.
Stir in sauce and simmer 10 minutes or until heated through.
Remove 1 cup of meat sauce and set aside.
Stir cooked twirls into remaining sauce.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use half of pecans in cheese ball and roll the cheese ball in the other half.

title: ensalada con carne(mexican salad with meat)
directions: In a heavy skillet, brown ground beef.
Add chopped onion, gravy mix and hot pepper sauce.
Stir in 3/4 cup water.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Brown beef and onion; salt and pepper.
Spread in pie pan.
Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs together in blender for about 15 seconds.
Pour over the meat in pie dish. Bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Remove from oven; cover with American cheese and tomato slices.
Return to oven for 6 to 8 minutes longer.
Remove from oven and add the Longhorn cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Cook pie shells and let cool.
Mix remaining ingredients together and add to shells.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Put in greased and floured bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: lakeland fudge cake
directions: Boil milk, butter and cocoa until bubbly.
Mix in nuts, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Spread over warm cake.

title: strip toffee sticks
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and rest of ingredients (except pecans) and mix well.
Press into 2 ungreased jelly-roll pans.
Spread with egg whites, pouring off excess.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans, pressing in slightly.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut into bars before completely cool. Remove from pans when cooled.
These keep well in the refrigerator.

title: cranberry salad ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add cold water and chill. Mix next 6 ingredients.
Fold into gelatin.
Pour into lightly oiled 10-cup ring mold.
Chill until set.
Fill center of ring with mayonnaise and garnish with orange slices.
Makes 18 to 20 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken until tender and cut into small cubes.
Mix soups and chilies to make sauce.
Add chicken and cheese.
Fill flour tortillas with mixture.
Place seam down in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° to 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: dilled oyster crackers
directions: Mix oil, garlic powder, Hidden Valley dressing and dill seed. Put crackers in long sheet pan, then pour mixture over crackers. Let stand, stirring occasionally.
Best, if left overnight, uncovered, then store in plastic containers.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine soup and sour cream and stir in carrots.
Fold in drained squash and onion. Combine stuffing and butter.
Spread 1/2 mix in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mix over stuffing.
Sprinkle rest of stuffing mix over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: june's choc-mallow pie
directions: Combine flour, cornstarch and sugar.
Mix eggs with 1 cup of milk and stir into flour and sugar mixture gradually over medium heat.

title: harvest hot tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; mix well.
Store in an airtight container.
Stir 2 teaspoons tea mix into 1 cup boiling water for each serving.

title: pickles
directions: Mix cukes, onions and salt; add enough water to cover.
Soak 3 to 4 hours.
Drain cukes.
Combine vinegar, sugar, mustard seed, turmeric, celery seed and cloves.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add cukes to liquid and reheat.
Do not boil.
Pack in hot jars.

title: chop-suey cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan, sprayed with Pam or Baker's Joy.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: russian apricot chicken
directions: Place chicken in single layer in baking dish.
Spoon apricot preserves over each piece of chicken.
Sprinkle with soup mix. Pour dressing over top.
Bake uncovered in a 325° oven for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: chili con queso y arroz
directions: Grease casserole.
Layer rice, chilies, sour cream and cheese (saving 1/2 cup cheese for topping).
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip fudge cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients. Fold in 1 cup sour cream and the chocolate chips.
Bake in Bundt pan 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: In Dutch oven, saute chopped onion and green pepper, cut in strips, in margarine for 3 minutes.
Add ground chuck and brown; add salt and sugar.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce and water. Heat mixture to boiling; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix in large bowl with a fork or spoon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carrot coins
directions: What are coins?
Cut your carrots in the size of coins. Carrots and other deep yellow vegetables have lots of Vitamin A, which is good for healthy eyes and skin.

title: surprize meatballs
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and 1/4 teaspoon of salt.
Add meat and mix well.
Drain pineapple, onion, olives, and mushrooms. Place in a shallow pan and bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Serve hot on cocktail picks with sauce.

title: tea cakes
directions: Roll out and cut.
Cook at 400° about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin ice cream pie
directions: Spoon ice cream into pie shell. Freeze until firm.

title: time-to-spare ribs
directions: You will need one large size oven cooking bag (14 x 20-inch)

title: olive pecan dip
directions: Blend all ingredients, add olive juice as needed for desired consistency.
Use as cracker spread or as dip for fresh vegetables.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Beat egg, water, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Mix all dry ingredients together on a platter.
Put chicken in egg mixture, then put into a strainer and drain off excess egg.
Add to bread crumb mixture.
Make sure each piece is well coated.
Deep fry in hot oil.

title: chicken-broccoli noodles
directions: In a skillet, cook noodles according to package directions. Add seasoning packets; drain off most of the liquid.
Stir in mushroom soup and milk.
Add chicken and broccoli.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 4 servings.
Cooking time: 20 minutes.

title: mixed fruit compote
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in orange juice and combined juices.
Chill gelatin until consistency of egg whites. Fold in fruits.
Yields 6 servings.

title: stuffed zucchini casserole
directions: Peel
and
slice zucchini.
Cook zucchini and onions in boiling
salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Add uncooked carrots.	Fold into drained zucchini mixture.
Set
aside.
Combine
stuffing mix and melted margarine. Spread 1/2 of stuffing mixture in the bottom of 12-inch Dutch oven.
Add	zucchini mixture and top with the remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake
for
minutes with 12 coals on top and 10 coals on the bottom.

title: "big max" secret sauce make alike
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add to your favorite burger along with pickle slices and lettuce.

title: hot to trot salsa
directions: Finely chop pepper and onion.
Add finely chopped tomato, seasoning salt and crushed red pepper.
Mix well.
Add salsa ketchup.
Mix until blended.
Makes 2 servings.

title: butter pecan bars
directions: Beat well.
Pour in greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions thin.
Mix cucumbers, onions and salt together.
Mix and store in refrigerator for two hours.
Drain but do not rinse.
Add vinegar and sugar and mix with onions and cucumbers.
Freeze in containers.

title: sticky buns
directions: Heat together the ingredients (don't boil).
Pour batter into greased cake pan.
Roll out 2 loaves of frozen bread dough (thawed).
Sprinkle bread with cinnamon.
Roll up and slice into rolls, about 1-inch thick.
Lay in syrup and bake until brown. Bake at 350°.
Turn onto foil while warm.

title: mushrooms maryland
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Wash and stem the mushrooms.
Dip the caps into melted butter and place upside down in a buttered baking dish.

Combine crabmeat, eggs, mayonnaise, scallions, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and half the bread crumbs. Fill mushroom caps with mixture. Sprinkle with remaining crumbs and butter. Bake 15 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: ground beef kabobs (round style)
directions: Use a large bowl to mix kabobs.
Mix ground beef, onions, tomatoes, garlic, coriander, ginger, pepper and masala mix by hand until completely mixed.
(May want to wear plastic gloves as the chili can sometimes burn your skin.)
If the mix does not look like it will stay together, add a beaten egg, but I usually do not use any egg.

title: cauliflower and broccoli hot dish
directions: Cook and drain vegetables.
Pour soup and Cheez Whiz over vegetables.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. You may add fried onions, as many as you prefer, the last five minutes of baking. This adds extra flavor to vegetables.

title: mexican lunch
directions: Saute sausage, onion and bell peppers until the meat is done; drain.
Combine sausage mixture with remaining ingredients (except cheese).
Spoon mixture into lightly greased 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: six week muffins
directions: Mix bran, sugar, flour, soda and salt in a large bowl.
Add eggs, shortening and buttermilk.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Batter may be stored covered in refrigerator up to 6 weeks.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: shrimp brennan
directions: Rinse shrimp in cold water.
In large iron skillet, add all ingredients.
Bring to boil, then turn down to simmer.
Simmer, uncovered, until shell is loose from the back of the shrimp. Serves 2 Cajuns or 6 city slickers.

title: deviled steak
directions: For sauce, combine catsup, water, Worcestershire sauce, dry mustard, salt and pepper.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter 5 minutes, then add seasonings, chicken, soup and sour cream.
Mix thoroughly.
Place cooked spaghetti into shallow casserole.
Top with chicken mix.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: reuben loaf
directions: Combine eggs, bread crumbs, parsley and garlic.
Stir in corned beef; mix well.
On foil or waxed paper, pat meat mixture to a 10 x 10-inch square.
Combine sauerkraut, caraway and shredded cheese; mound in center of meat mixture.
Wrap meat mixture around and over sauerkraut mixture, forming a loaf (be sure ends and seams are completely sealed).
Place loaf in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with cheese triangles; bake for 5 minutes more or until cheese is melted.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Combine first three ingredients in large bowl.
Mix with hands and shape mixture into five (4 x 1-inch) rolls.
Mixture will be very dry.
Put rolls in refrigerator and chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add sugar; cook for 1 minute, then add vinegar.
Turn down heat; cook until sugar dissolves.
Add cornstarch mixture, soy sauce and salt.
Stir until sauce thickens.

title: betty's brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in order; mix well. Spread in greased 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: lazy day lasagne
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Drain. Combine oregano with spaghetti sauce.
In greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish, alternate layers of noodles, cottage cheese, spaghetti sauce and Mozzarella cheese slices.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for about 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: popsicles
directions: Choose which kind of sicle to make.
Pour milk, juice or punch into cups.
Freeze about one hour and then add plastic spoon to the center.
Freeze until solid.
Peel cup away and enjoy a cool summer treat!

title: texas rice
directions: Mix all and bake at 350° for 1 hour or at 325° for 1/2 hour in a covered casserole.
To double, do not double salt.

title: lemony rhubarb glories
directions: Blend all together until fine crumbs and press into 8-inch square pan.
Cook at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place cut up chicken in bottom of 11 x 13-inch Pyrex bowl. Pour Veg-All over chicken.
Put mushroom and chicken soup in.
Mix biscuit mix and milk; pour over top of ingredients.
Spread butter over top and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican soup
directions: Cook pork meat in a stew pot.
Add enough water to cover pork. Simmer until tender.
Add salt, pepper, oregano and garlic.
When meat is cooked, add hominy and boil until kernels pop.
Add chili; stir.
Dice some onion and garnish.
Squeeze lemon juice onto bowl of posole.
Sprinkle oregano to taste.

title: stewed squid with peas
directions: Cut squid into strips.
Put the oil and garlic into a pan and heat.
When the garlic becomes golden, add the squid to the pan and season with salt and pepper.
Add the wine and let the mixture simmer for a few minutes.
Then add the anchovy fillets, the pureed tomatoes and enough water to cover the squid.
Cover and cook for about 20 minutes, then add the peas.
When the peas and squid are tender, remove the pan from the heat. Garnish with chopped parsley just before serving.
Serves 6.

title: instant potato lefse
directions: Heat water to boiling with margarine melting in it.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Chill.

title: country ham 'n cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, cheese, ham and seasonings.
Add flour and blend well.
Pinch dough off and roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes; serve hot.
Makes about 3 or 4 dozen.

title: spanish rice with beef
directions: Brown ground beef, breaking the pieces and stirring, about 5 minutes.
Add chopped onion, green pepper and celery.
Add water, tomatoes and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer on low until tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Add corn.
Stir in rice and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pour pie filling into pan.
In medium bowl, add flour, oats, brown sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well.
Cut in 1 stick of margarine.
Mix until crumbly.
Pour crumb mixture over apples.
Place in oven and bake for about 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed and drain.
Add soup, grated cheese, mayonnaise and eggs.
Fold in 3 ounces onion garlic croutons.
Turn into baking dish.
Sprinkle top with croutons.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: instant cocoa
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.
Use 1/3 cup in boiling water per serving.

title: squash delicious
directions: Combine sour cream, soup, carrot and 1/2 stick butter.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Don't boil.
Boil squash, onion and 1/2 stick of butter in a small amount of water until fork-tender. Drain.
Layer squash, sauce and stuffing mix in a 3-quart casserole, ending with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° until bubbly. Yields 8 servings.

title: orange chicken salad
directions: Make dressing by finely shredding 1/2 teaspoon of orange rind. Peel orange and section.
Catch juice.
Mix juice rind, honey, yogurt and poppy seed.
Chill.
Toss orange section grapes, nuts, celery and chicken.
Spoon on lettuce or spinach leaves.
Spoon dressing on top.
Makes 2 servings.
Double for 4.

title: caponata
directions: Cut
eggplants into half-inch cubes.
Heat 1/2 of olive oil in
large
pot
or Dutch oven.
Cook eggplant over medium heat until light brown; add onion and celery.
Cook just until soft. Remove
from
pan
and set aside.

title: beef cubes gourmet
directions: Brown meat in a small amount of melted shortening in large, heavy frying pan; add seasoning and water.
Cover and simmer until tender, 40 minutes.
Add more water if needed.
Stir in steak sauce and peas; heat thoroughly and remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve over buttered noodles or rice.

title: harold's caramels
directions: Cook to soft ball.
Add pecans and cool.
Cut into small pieces.
Wrap.

title: patty's dip
directions: Drain well and chop in food processor coarsely. Spread in quiche pan. Spread over thin layer of mayo. Top with shredded Monterey Jack cheese. Heat at 350° until cheese melts.

title: five vegetable casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender.
Drain, cool slightly and slice.
Cook cauliflower, carrots and onion in boiling water until tender, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain.
Place all vegetables in a 2-quart baking dish.
Stir together soup and milk. Spoon over vegetables.
Bake covered in a 350° oven 30 to 35 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 3 to 4 minutes more or until cheese melts.

title: impossible coconut custard pie
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar.
Add the eggs, milk and vanilla and cream again.
Mix in coconut and the Bisquick; stir well.
Pour into a 9-inch pie pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let set.
When salad has set, mix two 3 ounce packages of cream cheese with 2 tablespoons of mayonnaise and enough milk to make it spread easily on top of salad.
This is good at holidays.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Drain again. Mash egg yolks and mix with mustard until smooth.
Add sugar, vinegar, mayonnaise, onion and celery.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugars, butter and milk for 3 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.
Chill until firm.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and let stand one hour.
Mix shortening and sugars well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Blend in eggs and raisins.
Add oatmeal and chopped nuts.
Drop by heaping teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: rhubarb walnut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together both sugars with the oil. Beat in eggs well. Add milk and mix. Stir in remaining ingredients except final two.
Mix batter well until smooth.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Top each with 1 teaspoon melted butter and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Bake for 1 hour or until a cake tester comes out dry.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel apples; slice thin and place in large bowl. Add sugar; toss and let stand 15 minutes.
Mix dry ingredients; add to apples.
Stir to coat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir by hand to mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.
Top with vanilla ice cream and Cool Whip.
Store uncovered.

title: egg roll filling
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine chicken, cornstarch, soy sauce and ginger.
Blend.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Heat oil in wok. Stir-fry mushrooms about 1 minute.
Add chicken and continue to stir-fry until firm and white.
Add remaining ingredients and stir-fry until cabbage is crisp-tender.
Cool before filling egg roll wrappers.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain corn.
Melt oleo in casserole dish.
Add the flour and stir.
Add drained corn and carton of whipping cream.
Cook at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: apple strudel
directions: Roll out pastry dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Peel and slice apples.
Spread over pastry.
Sprinkle with sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Place in greased loaf pan. Cover with milk.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes, until well browned.
Delicious eaten as a dessert or an accompaniment for a main meal.

title: nathan's baked beans
directions: Combine everything but bacon.
Pour in a large casserole dish. Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meal in a frying pan
directions: Brown onion and ground beef in oil; add other ingredients. Simmer for about 15 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown rice in margarine until golden brown. Remove from heat and add soup, mushrooms, chestnuts and water. Liquid from mushrooms and chestnuts can be used for part of the water. Place in casserole and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: low-fat homemade ice cream
directions: Combine the egg substitute, sugar and milk.
Heat until the mixture bubbles, stirring often, or until it is a soft custard. Beat the egg whites stiff.
Over them pour the hot custard and mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla and salt; cool, then add cream.
Mix well.
Freeze.

title: potatoes casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in a baking dish.
Put the cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: stifado (a "southern" greek stew)
directions: Brown beef in butter in Dutch oven or large saucepan.
Add onions, tomato paste, water, salt, pepper and cinnamon.
Cover; boil and lower heat.
Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours until meat is tender.
Add carrots and potatoes.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes until vegetables are tender.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together and pour in 2 graham cracker crust pie shells.

title: one pot bean dish(calico beans)
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, drain fat.
Put in crock-pot. Brown bacon and onions, drain fat.
Put in crock-pot with beef. Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Cover and cook on low 4 to 6 hours.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: maple cream
directions: In a large pan over high heat, bring cream and maple syrup to a boil. Reduce to medium-low and simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Stir occasionally until slightly thick. Serve warm or cold.

title: macaroni and beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Cook macaroni in 1/4 stick of butter in boiling water until tender.
In baking dish, put half of the macaroni, ground beef, cheese and catsup.
Add remainder of all ingredients and top with remainder of cheese. Cook in a 300° oven until cheese browns.

title: marinated garden tortellini salad(yield:  6 1-cup servings)
directions: 1. Cook tortellini to desired doneness, as directed on package, adding broccoli during last minute of cooking time.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Add egg yolks and enough of the milk to make a paste.
Add rest of milk; stir.
Microwave 5 minutes; stir.
Microwave 2 minutes more; stir.
Do this until thick.
Add vanilla and butter.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Put meringue on top; broil until brown.

title: chicken and broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a pie plate.
Mix broccoli, 2 cups cheese, chicken and onion in pie plate.
Beat milk, eggs, baking mix, salt and pepper for 1 minute on high speed.
Pour over mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well and squeeze to remove excess water.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Stir cream cheese until smooth, gradually add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate for about 15 minutes, until able to shape into ball, roll in pecans.
Flavor is better if chilled overnight, also freezes well.

title: turtle brownies
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk slowly over low heat.
Combine cake mix, butter, nuts and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Spread half of batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan that is greased and floured.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Spread caramel mixture over chips.
Drop remaining batter with a spoon on top of caramel, spacing evenly. Bake 15 to 18 minutes longer.
Do not overbake.
These will be chewy but delicious!

title: anise cookies
directions: Use part of flour to flour anise seed.
Mix ingredients.
Roll out and cut.
Sugar tops and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix frozen meatballs, chili sauce, jelly, and sugar in a crock pot. Cook on low for 6 hours.

title: doughnuts
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven pan until 375°.
Press hole in center with thumb (ketchup lids work great too!).
Place doughnut in hot oil.
Fry until brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Roll in sugars or top with favorite topping.

title: little brown church-never fail pie crust
directions: Combine flour, cornstarch, salt, sugar, baking powder and lard or vegetable shortening.
Cut until crumbly.
Combine mixture with water and vinegar.

title: kathy's chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar, chocolate and vanilla.
Beat 1 egg separately until light and then add to mixture.
Beat very well. Beat other egg and repeat procedure.
Beat until creamy and smooth.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill well before serving (overnight if possible).
Top with whipped cream and garnish with almond slivers (toasted) and chocolate shavings.

title: tongue with tahini
directions: Boil tongue in salt water.
Tongue is done when easily pierced with a fork.
Remove from pan and skin.
Skin will peel easily; cool.
Slice tongue and arrange on lettuce in serving platter. Add tahini dressing over tongue.
Decorate with parsley.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix first six ingredients together, then add flour and nuts. Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sausage upside-down cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook sausage, onion and pepper in skillet until brown and crumbly.
Stir in flour and mix in next four ingredients.
Remove from heat, stir in cheese and olives. Spread evenly in 9-inch square pan.
Prepare muffin mix and spread over sausage.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand in pan 5 minutes.

title: special k treats
directions: Melt in microwave in large bowl. Add 6 cups Special K cereal. Stir
and spread on cookie sheet. Makes a great after school treat.

title: grandma bernardini's "speddini"
directions: Thinly slice meat across grain and cut into strips approximately 1-inch wide and 3-inches long.
Mix in bowl, bread crumbs, Parmesan, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Dredge meat slices into crumb mixture, making sure both sides are coated.
Roll strips and put on (metal) skewers.
Generously baste with olive oil.
Place under broiler until browned on each side.

title: picante sauce
directions: Combine in large pan and cook for 30 to 45 minutes as it will thicken.
Water bath for 20 minutes, long enough to make sure it seals.

title: kay cline's monkey bread recipe
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; let stand. Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup of warm water.
Beat eggs and mix with all ingredients.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour and mix well.
Continue adding up to 6 cups of flour.
Cover bowl and let rise. Refrigerate overnight.

title: aunt vivian's heavenly hash
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan, scatter out marshmallows.
In a saucepan, melt chocolate chips, Eagle Brand milk and plain milk on low heat.
After melted, add chopped nuts to chocolate.
Stir nuts in then pour over marshmallows.
Let set to cool, cut in squares.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add enough mayonnaise to make good mixture.

title: miniature pecan pies
directions: Let cream cheese and margarine stand at room temperature and then mix together thoroughly.
Add flour.
Chill overnight. Divide pastry into 24 balls and press into miniature muffin tins.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Leave in refrigerator until hard.
Form into ball and roll in walnuts.

title: tortellini salad(yield:  6 cups)
directions: Combine olive oil with the next 6 ingredients in a glass jar. Let stand 30 minutes.
Mix with all remaining ingredients in 1 1/2-quart serving dish.
Chill until serving time.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: This is better cut into small pieces.

title: seven-in-one-casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and have ready for casserole.
Put layer of potatoes, then a layer of onion, carrots and celery.
Take juice from peas, mix with soup.
Pour peas over celery.
Put meat on top of peas.
Pour pea juice mixture on top of meat.
Bake about 1 hour at 375°.

title: cherry rice salad
directions: Cook rice and drain.
In a large bowl, mix rice and rest of ingredients and cover tightly.
Refrigerate.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant and cut in chunks. Cook until tender in just enough water to prevent burning.
Drain excess water after it is cooked (there shouldn't be any). Add butter, salt and pepper. Allow to cool. Beat egg yolks and add them along with other ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then fold them in last. Pour into greased casserole and bake in a 400° oven until golden brown on top. Good-good.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Drain.
Rinse with hot water.
In large pot, melt butter.
Stir in cream and pepper.
Cook on low heat until slightly thickened, 5 minutes or so.
Stir in cheese and continue stirring until cheese melts.
Immediately add noodles. Toss to coat.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Thaw broccoli and mix all ingredients together.
Bake according to Jiffy package directions.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Salt and cook the cabbage with very little water until tender. Drain.
Grease a baking dish.
Alternate a layer of cabbage, a layer of combined cheeses and then white sauce.
End with cheese and sprinkle with cornflake crumbs.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: reception cookies
directions: Combine caramels and milk in medium saucepan.
Heat until caramels are melted.
Combine Bisquick, oats, sugar and butter. Blend well.
Press half the oat mixture on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a huge bowl, mix dry ingredients. Add eggs, oil and milk.
Mix with a large spoon.
Grease muffin tins.
Bake 20 minutes in a preheated 400° oven.
This batter will keep up to 6 weeks in the refrigerator.
Therefore, bake 6 to 12 at a time each day.

title: almond tea
directions: Boil sugar and water together and add rest of ingredients. Serve hot.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and spoon into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Keep cold in refrigerator.

title: mandy's homemade pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour pancake dough on a hot greased skillet.

title: doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Add milk, 1/2 cup sugar, the salt, eggs, shortening and 2 cups of the flour. Beat on low speed for 30 seconds, then beat for 2 minutes on medium speed, scraping sides of bowl.
Stir in remaining flour until smooth.
Cover; let rise in warm place until double (50 to 60 minutes).
Turn dough onto floured surface.
Roll dough until it is 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured doughnut cutter.
Cover; let rise 30 to 40 minutes.
Heat vegetable oil in deep fryer. Drop doughnuts in hot oil.
When they rise to surface, turn and cook on other side.

title: apple crisp
directions: This is a delicious and good way to use surplus lemons.
Those rare souls who like ginger will appreciate this pie.

title: german pancakes
directions: Heat oven to 425 degrees. Grease 9 x 11 pan. Mix eggs & milk with mixer. Add flour, then butter. Mix on high until well blended.

title: summer salmon pasta
directions: Drain salmon.
Saute onion, carrot, beans, squash and mushrooms for 4 minutes.
Add salmon, tomato, peas, seasonings and cream.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add spaghetti; toss until thoroughly coated.
Add 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.

title: mexican pasta salad
directions: Prepare pasta according to package.
Drain.
In large bowl, combine pasta and oil; toss gently to coat well.
Add kidney beans, chickpeas, olives, escarole and salsa.
Toss, chill and serve.

title: short cut strata
directions: Arrange croutons on bottom of pan.
Grate cheese over croutons.
Beat eggs together with half and half.
Pour over croutons and cheese.
Let all set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Good brunch dish.

title: saucy stroganoff
directions: In skillet, cook ground beef or pork and onion until meat is browned.
Drain off fat.
Stir in mushrooms, bouillon granules, Worcestershire sauce, 1 1/2 cups water, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Combine sour cream and flour. Gradually blend some of the hot beef mixture into sour cream. Return to skillet. Cook and stir in catsup.
Heat through. Serve over hot cooked noodles.
Sprinkle with snipped parsley, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle corn flakes or chips on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: dirt cake
directions: Will need 8-inch plastic flower pot, trowel, bunch of silk flowers and 1 package of gummy worms.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredient well. Reserve a small amount of tomato paste to put on top. Roll into a loaf. Add a small amount of water to baking dish and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Wait about 5 minutes before slicing.

title: raspberry delight
directions: Mix lemonade according to directions. Chill until icy cold. Spoon sherbet into tall glasses.
Pour lemonade over.
Before serving, top with whipped topping. Top with a cherry.

title: quick caramel rolls
directions: Mix cinnamon and white and brown sugars. Roll each biscuit in this mixture. Stand biscuits upright in well-greased Bundt pan, one at a time. Pour remaining sugar mixture over biscuits. Melt margarine (butter) and pour over biscuits. Drop ice cream by teaspoonfuls over the biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: parisienne prime rib
directions: Combine tenderizer and olive oil.
With meat in a large bowl, rub this all over and into meat.
Mix all the herbs and spices together and place on a wax paper.
Roll meat in this mixture, patting to help it stick to meat.
Bake 1 3/4 hours until meat thermometer reaches 160° for medium.
Serve with baked potatoes.

title: mary's divinity
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until it hardens when dropped in cup of cold water.
Beat 2 egg whites.
Beat in syrup a little at a time until real fluffy.
Then add more rapidly.
Continue beating until semi-cool.
Add vanilla and continue for a few minutes.
Then stir in nuts and spoon out or spread on a sheet. Cut out into squares.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix eggs and sugar in large bowl.
Stir baking soda into flour.
Add flour mixture alternately with pineapple.
Add nuts. Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: judy's kabobs
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Mix other ingredients and marinate chicken 1 hour.
Refrigerate at this time.
After 1 hour, on skewers, alternate chicken strips with pineapple rings in "s" curve.
Cook on medium to low heated grill for 25 to 35 minutes. Turn frequently and baste with sauce.
Do not overcook.

title: foiled chicken(yield:  4 servings)
directions: 1. Cut 4-5 18 - 20-inch pieces of foil.

title: party punch
directions: Blend Kool-Aid, sugar and water and punch and juice.
Chill. Add chilled ginger ale or Sprite just before serving.
Serves 35 to 40 servings.

title: lemon 4-layer delight
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Blend and pat into a 9 x 11-inch pan for crust.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: crab imperial
directions: Remove all cartilage from real crabmeat or rinse Crab Delights. In medium size saucepan, melt butter; mix in flour.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly to keep mixture smooth and lump free. Cook, stirring over medium heat until mixture comes to boil and thickens.
Mix in onion, Worcestershire sauce and bread cubes; cool.
Fold in mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
In another pan, heat butter slightly until lightly browned.
Add crabmeat and toss.
Combine with sauce mixture.
Put in individual shells or 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle paprika and bake at 450° until hot, bubbly and light brown on top, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating in well.
Add buttermilk alternately with flour to which salt has been added, beating well.
Mix to a paste cocoa and 1/2 cup hot water.
Add soda to other 1/2 cup hot water.
Add both to mixture. After mixing it will seem rather thin, but that is as it should be.
Bake in 3 (8-inch) pans or 2 (9-inch) pans which have been greased and lined with wax paper at 350° until testing done with a toothpick.
Frost with 7 Minute Frosting.
Cover with shredded coconut.

title: frozen strawberry daiquiri mix
directions: Combine sugar, lime juice and water in bowl. Stir to mix, and then let stand until sugar is almost completely dissolved, about 15 minutes (mixture will be thick).

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Pour this mixture into chicken broth (chicken removed).
Stir to mix well.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in cut up chicken (bite-size pieces) and add vegetables.
Heat until bubbly.
Pour mixture into baking dish.
Top with pie crust or biscuits.
Bake at 350 degrees until crust browns.

title: butter pecan dessert
directions: Mix crackers with melted oleo.
Put 1/2 in 9 x 12-inch pan. Beat pudding with milk for 2 minutes, then mix ice cream with pudding.
Pour over crumbs.
Spread Cool Whip over the top.
Top with the other 1/2 of crumbs.
Serves 16.

title: pigs in blankets
directions: Combine rice, beef, egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Steam cabbage until leaves are pliable; reserve water.
Carefully peel off the cabbage leaves.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Boil sugar, cornstarch and water until thick.
Remove from heat and add strawberry jello.
Cool in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Add sliced strawberries into baked pie shells.
Refrigerate until set. Top with Cool Whip and serve.

title: rice and gravy
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon oil.
Make sure you brown the meat real good because that is what makes the gravy brown.
Add your garlic, seasoned salt, parsley, black pepper and banana pepper.
Add water to cover and add 1 can of brown gravy and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix everything except ginger ale.
Freeze 24 hours.
Take out 1/2 hour to 1 hour before use and mash until slushy.
Add ginger ale.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
Cool, peel and slice.
Mix the 7 ingredients until well blended.
Alternate a layer of potatoes, then a layer of dressing.

title: farm-style potato frittata
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Set aside.
Heat 2 tablespoons of drippings in 10-inch skillet.
Add potatoes; cover and saute over medium heat, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes, or until tender.
Uncover and brown.
(Add more drippings if necessary.) Sprinkle
lightly with salt and pepper.
Add onions and green pepper.
Saute for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Beat eggs with water, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Pour over ingredients in skillet.
Cook as for an omelette, lifting edges to allow uncooked egg to run under.
When firm and browned on bottom, sprinkle with cheese and bacon.
Cover for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: white gravy for dumplings
directions: Place cut up onion in a little hot oil and saute.
Add cream, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat to its lowest setting, never boiling.
Heat it for 1 hour and pour over dumplings, noodles or potatoes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix into balls about the size of walnuts and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in greased loaf pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake 45 minutes, uncovered, for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: granny's pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, toss well. Sprinkle parmesan cheese over top.
Before serving, mix again.

title: fudge sundae pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and stir over medium heat until melted. Cool to room temperature.

Line pie pan with vanilla wafers. Cover wafers with a layer of vanilla ice cream, then spoon half of the chocolate mixture over ice cream. Cover with more ice cream and top with remaining chocolate mixture.
Keep in freezer until ready to serve.

title: fried pie dough
directions: Sift the dry ingredients.
Cut shortening in until like cornmeal.
Put beaten egg in 1 cup measure.
Add evaporated milk to measure 1 cup.
Add to the mixture.
Mix until dough pulls away from the bowl.
Knead lightly.
Wrap tightly in plastic wrap and chill overnight.

title: the best beef stew
directions: Pat dry all of the beef cubes (important because the meat will brown quite well this way); season the meat with a mixture of the salt and pepper. Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a Dutch oven until it is quite hot but not smoking. Arrange the meat in a single layer; don't crowd the meat and brown it well on all sides. This may take 2 or 3 separate brownings.

title: sherried mushrooms
directions: Briefly saute mushrooms in melted butter or margarine and then add sherry and soy sauce.
Turn heat very low and continue to simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Mushrooms will absorb liquid.

title: tomato salsa fiesta
directions: Combine first four ingredients, beat in oil. Gently toss with remaining ingredients. Marinate at room temperature for 1 hour.

title: italian meat loaf patties
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Set aside half of the sauce to brush on patties. In a large bowl, combine remaining sauce with remaining ingredients. Mix with fork. On large greased baking sheet, shape meat mixture into 8 (1-inch thick) oblong patties. Brush with reserved sauce over patties. Bake 20 minutes or until done. Serve patties with hot buttered noodles.

title: artichoke pie
directions: Boil artichokes in water for 20 minutes. Drain well. In bowl, mix artichokes, beaten eggs, Mozzarella cheese, grated cheese, salt, pepper, parsley and basil. Mix well. Sprinkle pie crust bottom with bread crumbs and add artichoke mixture. Dot top of pie with butter. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until bubbling. Serves 6 to 8.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and drain.
Add chili powder and cans.
Mix well and bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: brie with sun dried tomatoes
directions: Remove rind from the Brie with a sharp knife and put the Brie on a serving plate.

title: autumn coffee
directions: In small bowl, stir together sugar and spices.
Stir into coffee.
Into each of 6 mugs, pour 1 cup coffee and a generous tablespoon warm milk; stir.
Sprinkle with an additional dash of ground cinnamon, if desired.

title: one-bowl brownies
directions: Melt chocolate squares or cocoa substitute with oleo.
Stir well.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir.
Add flour and nuts. Mix. Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool.
Cut into 24 squares.
Serve.

title: republican dessert
directions: Combine flour, margarine, 2 tablespoons powdered sugar and nuts and press into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cauliflower soup(for nonfat diets)
directions: Put all ingredients in pot; cook 15 to 20 minutes, until cauliflower is soft.
Let cool, then puree in blender or use potato masher.
Will keep in refrigerator about 3 days or can be frozen.

title: easy waldorf salad
directions: Throw celery, fruits and nuts into a bowl.
If you have a fancy glass bowl, use it.
Mix the mayonnaise and lemon juice together; add to the fruit.
Toss lightly with serving spoons. Chill in the refrigerator for about 1/2 hour and serve.

title: mexican chicken-corn chowder
directions: Melt butter in a Dutch oven over medium-high heat.
Add chicken, onion and garlic and saut 10 minutes.
Stir in next 7 ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring often, 15 minutes.
Stir in 2 tablespoons cilantro.
Yield:
2 quarts.
Prep:
20 minutes. Cook:
30 minutes.
Garnishes:
chopped fresh cilantro and Anaheim chile.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
In saucepan, put margarine, all-purpose flour and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly and adding milk gradually (to make smooth).
Cut off heat and then add the cream cheese to mixture.

title: molasses crinkle cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cream the shortening, butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and molasses; blend well.
Add dry ingredients gradually; mix well.
Chill.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Dip tops in granulated sugar.
Flatten slightly; place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: blue cheese salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender and blend for 1 minute. Stir in 1 package of crumbled Blue cheese.

title: cajun pecans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 3 1/2-quart slow cooker.
Cover; slow cook on high (300°) for 15 minutes.
Reduce the heat to low (200°); continue to slow cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 2 hours.
Transfer the nuts to a baking sheet; cool completely before serving.

title: capellini with fresh tomato
directions: Mix all ingredients except pasta and Parmesan in a large bowl. Cook pasta, al dente, according to package directions.
Drain pasta and add to sauce in large bowl.
Toss well.
Cool to room temperature before serving.
Serve grated Parmesan on the side.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Put the sugar, milk, butter, cocoa and salt in a large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in the rolled oats, vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Drop from a teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Makes 48.

title: dingbats
directions: Cook dates and next 4 ingredients about 10 minutes.
Pour over cereal and nuts and mix together.
When cool enough to handle, grease hands and make small balls.
Roll balls in coconut. Store in airtight container to prevent drying out.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: clam chowder
directions: Boil water; add chopped onion.
Cut up potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add clams and evaporated milk.
Heat until hot and serve.

title: mock chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and serve on lettuce.
Also excellent for sandwich filling or to fill pastry shells.

title: apricot jello
directions: Drain pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Mix all ingredients together using dry jello.
There will be plenty liquid in other items for the dry jello.
Mix well and refrigerate until it sets up and serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Stir in sugars, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir into zucchini mixture until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove to wire rack.
Cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: cinnamon roll-ups(easy and wonderful!)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: baked pork chops supreme
directions: In a skillet, heat oil.
Fry pork chops until brown.
Remove from pan and drain.
Saute onions and peppers until tender.
Place chops in casserole dish.
On each chop place 1/2 cup rice, some onions and pepper.
In a bowl, mix remaining ingredients; pour over chops and rice mixture.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lentil harvest casserole
directions: Combine rice, 2 cups of water and salt in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer covered 15 to 18 minutes (longer for brown rice) or until all water is absorbed and rice is tender.

title: barbecued beef roast
directions: Pierce meat thoroughly with fork.
Place in cooking bag.
Add sauce.
Close bag loosely with strip cut from end of bag. Marinate for 3 to 4 hours or overnight in refrigerator.

title: famous chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together margarine, sugars, egg, water and vanilla until creamy.
Add combined remaining dry ingredients; mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: crab and eggs
directions: Melt butter in ovenproof skillet. Add onion and tomatoes. Saute until onion is soft. Pour eggs into mixture; season. Cook until eggs have almost congealed. Stir in crab meat (cut in cubes) and cream cheese. Bake in 400° oven for about 10 minutes until cheese is melted and eggs are congealed.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Chop chicken breast halves into bite-size.
Fry in the 2 tablespoons of oil.
In another frying pan, add frozen California Blend vegetables.
Stir-fry.
Add chicken, then cream of mushroom soup, milk and Choy sauce.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: cantonese beef
directions: Brown meat and onion until done.
Add next 3 ingredients, mixing in.
Make a well in center of pan, adding vegetables. Bring to a boil and mix together.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes, covered.
Serves 4.

title: chile con queso (mas o menos)(mas o menos = more or less)
directions: These quantities are approximate.
Use however much of
the "mas o menos" items to get the desired degree of hot or spicy. Beware, cooking the chilies in butter will make them hotter!

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend cake mix, oil, water and eggs.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
(Top of cookies may look pale.)

title: squash casserole
directions: In an 8 x 8-inch casserole dish, cover bottom with bread crumbs and butter.
Mix together soup, onion, pimiento, sour cream, salt and pepper and pour over top of bread crumbs.
Top with additional bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: southern pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan or Bundt pan. Measure butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla into large mixing bowl. Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 5 minutes on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
On low speed, mix in flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk.
Pour into pan.
Bake 70 to 80 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan about 20 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: peach slush
directions: Put all ingredients in the blender and mix.
Freeze.
Mix with 7-Up or ginger ale.

title: mom's chicken rivel soup
directions: Cook chicken with water to cover and 2 teaspoons salt until done (or salt to taste).
Take chicken out; set aside.
Beat egg with 1/4 teaspoon of salt.
Add flour and mix quickly with a fork until batter forms very small pieces.
Add rivels slowly to boiling chicken broth.
Stir and simmer gently for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add chicken taken from the bones and serve.
Recipe for rivels may easily be doubled.
Canned chicken broth may be used in place of cooked chicken and broth.

title: swiss cheese party rye
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Broil one side of Pepperidge Farm rye until slightly brown.
Turn; spread with mixture.
Place piece of Swiss cheese on top of each rye and broil.

title: vanilla almond crunch
directions: Toast almonds in butter.
Remove half of almonds and set aside.
Combine cereal, brown sugar, coconut and salt with remaining almonds and butter.
Pat mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Spread ice cream over cooled crust.
Decorate top with reserved almonds.
Freeze until firm.
Cover tight.
Yields 10 servings.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and blend.
Mix in egg. Add vanilla, milk, baking powder, soda and salt.
Blend well.
Stir in flour and oats. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: chinese meat loaf
directions: In saucepan, mix tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Combine remaining ingredients in separate dish.
Add 1/2 cup tomato sauce mixture.
Mix and shape in an uncovered pan.
Pour remaining sauce over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (basting frequently).

title: orange-strawberry sponge cake
directions: Combine flour and 1/3 cup sugar.
Set aside.
In a small mixer bowl, beat egg yolks with an electric mixer on high speed about 5 minutes or until thick and lemon colored.
Combine 3 teaspoons of the shredded orange peel and the orange juice.
Add to beaten egg yolks, beating on low speed until combined.
Gradually add the 2/3 cup sugar and salt, beating on medium speed until sugar dissolves. Gradually add about 1/4 of the flour mixture to yolk mixture, beating on low speed until combined.
Repeat with remaining flour mixture, 1/4 at a time, beating a total of about 2 minutes.

title: deviled corned beef buns
directions: Flake corned beef; mix with remaining ingredients, except buns.
Spread in buns, wrap in foil and heat at 350° for 20 minutes.
Prepare early and bake just before serving if you wish. Makes 8 buns.

title: powdered sugar cookies
directions: Mix first five ingredients together, then add dry ingredients. Mix well.
Chill a few hours or overnight.

title: chicken corn chowder
directions: Add potato, carrot, onion, celery, corn, broth, water, salt and pepper in Dutch oven.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer until tender, about 10 minutes.
Shake flour and milk in tightly covered container; gradually stir into hot mixture.
Heat to boiling. Boil 1 minute. Stir in chicken and remaining milk. Heat over low heat, stirring occasionally, just until hot, about 10 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Combine and toast first 5 ingredients in 300° oven for 1/2 hour.
Stir often and watch closely.
Allow to cool.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put half of Rice Krispies mixture on bottom; spread ice cream on top.
Cover with remaining mixture.
Cover air tightly and return to freezer.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat soup and milk until soup is dissolved and smooth.
Then place layer of potatoes, onion and soup mix.
Sprinkle sugar, salt and pepper on each layer.
Just dot butter on each layer also. Bake at 350° to 400° until potatoes are tender.
If in a hurry, cook potatoes a few minutes first.

title: "save the labels" chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in boiling water for 20 minutes.
Prepare stuffing per package.
Cut cooled chicken into bite size pieces. Mix all ingredients.
Add peas and carrots and mushrooms last. Cook at 350° for 30 to 40
minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and place in buttered casserole alternately with the other ingredients.
Top with bread crumbs; dot with butter. Bake for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: brisket
directions: Place brisket in baking dish.
Sprinkle onion soup on top. Drizzle mixture of Worcestershire sauce and liquid smoke over top. Wrap in double layers of foil or heavy foil.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Continue baking at 250° for a minimum of 7 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute pepper and onion in margarine.
Mix with all other ingredients and bake at 300° about 45 minutes.
When almost done, sprinkle with grated cheese.
Put back in oven long enough to melt the cheese.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt butter.
Beat eggs, then pour all into blender.
Blend for 7 minutes continuously.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: marshmallow popcorn balls
directions: Pop corn and pour into big roasting pan.
Melt butter and marshmallows in saucepan.
Pour over popcorn, a little at a time, stirring until all corn is covered.
Wrap in Saran Wrap.
Makes about 40 medium size balls.

title: chicken breasts with peach chutney
directions: Pound chicken breasts to make thinner.
Brown in olive oil. Add onions, garlic, pepper and chutney.
Cover and cook until chicken is done, 3 to 5 minutes.
Uncover; add cream and cook a little more until sauce thickens.
Serves 2 or 3.

title: irish cream balls
directions: Crush the vanilla waters.
A food processor is the fastest for this.
Melt the chocolate and add to the crushed wafers, along with the liqueur.
Roll into small balls and roll in coconut to coat.
Refrigerate to set, then pack in containers and keep refrigerated.

title: dick's dumplings
directions: Mix flour and salt; cut in shortening.
Add egg and water; mix to moisten well.
You may need to add slightly more water.
Roll out dough 1/4-inch thick and cut into squares.
Drop in hot bean soup.
Cook, covered, about 15 minutes.
May also be used in chicken broth.

title: cavatini
directions: Saute in skillet until sausage is browned.
Drain fat.
Add 2 to 3 (32 ounce) jars chunky garden style spaghetti sauce; simmer. Meanwhile, cook pasta in 3 shapes.
(I use elbow macaroni, twist macaroni and mini shells, but you can use any type you prefer.) Cook about 2 pounds total pasta.
Drain pasta.
In large casserole dish (9 x 13-inch), layer pasta, sauce, pasta, sauce.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until cheese melts and is bubbly.

title: whopper pie
directions: Combine ice cream and Cool Whip until blended.
Save 8 Whoppers and crush remaining candy.
Add 1 cup crushed candy to ice cream mixture.
Spoon into crust.
Top with remaining candy.
Freeze 4 hours.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar. Blend in peanut butter and Cool Whip. Spread 1/2 of mixture in 2 crumb crusts. Drizzle with fudge topping. Spread remaining 1/2 of mixture on top. Drizzle with fudge topping or chocolate syrup. Freeze or refrigerate.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine the ingredients in 3-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 2 cups cornflakes and 1/4 cup melted margarine, combined.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yo do not need to defrost the potatoes.
Freezes well.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Make a frosting glaze of powdered sugar, water and vanilla.

title: pineapple salsa
directions: Combine pineapple, red pepper, ginger, lime juice, cloves, cilantro and liquid red seasoning in small bowl; toss to combine. Refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Serve with chicken.

title: pastel molded eggs
directions: Blend marshmallow cream, almond extract and margarine with mixer.
Gradually add rest of ingredients.
Work dough with hands forming egg or desired shapes.
Refrigerate overnight, dip in melted chocolate and decorate as desired.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: In medium salad bowl combine peas, onions, green pepper and garlic.
Stir together all remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Chill covered for at least 12 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: caramel layer chocolate squares
directions: In heavy pan, combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk. Cook over low heat.
Stir constantly until caramels are melted. Set aside.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, butter, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and nuts.
Stir by hand until it holds together. Press half of dough into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Reserve rest of dough for top.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Sprinkle chocolate chips over baked crust.
Spread caramels over chocolate pieces.
Crumble rest of dough over caramels mixture. Return to oven and bake for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool slightly, then refrigerate 30 minutes to set caramels.
Yields 36 bars.

title: wild rice and chicken casserole
directions: Prepare rice mix.
Cook onion and celery in butter.
Stir in soup, sour cream, wine and curry powder.
Stir in chicken and cooked rice.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Stir before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: "chex party mix"
directions: Melt margarine in open roasting pan in preheated 250° oven. Stir in seasonings. Gradually add cereals, nuts and pretzels; stir to coat evenly. Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Spread on absorbent paper to cool. Store in large zipper bag.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Marinate meat in wine for 1/2 hour at room temperature.
In 5-quart casserole, mix remaining ingredients and add meat mixture. Bake at 275° for 4 hours.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: yankee corn sticks
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In another bowl, mix eggs, milk and oil.
Add to flour mixture.
Beat just until smooth.
Spoon batter into hot, greased cast-iron corn stick pans.
Fill 2/3 full each.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 20 sticks.

title: bite size crab cakes
directions: Pick over crab meat to remove any pieces of shell.
Mince red or green pepper and celery; place in medium bowl with crab meat. Grate onion; add to crab meat.
Add eggs, bread crumbs, mustard, Worcestershire, mayonnaise and hot pepper sauce; mix well.
Shape crab mixture into oval patties using approximately 2 teaspoons of mixture for each patty.
Place patties on large platter, cover and refrigerate.
About 20 minutes prior to serving, in 12-inch skillet over medium heat, add butter and cooking oil.
Cook 1/3 of crab cakes until brown on both sides, drain and keep warm until all crab cakes are cooked.
Serve with your favorite seafood cocktail or tartar sauce.

title: berry sauce
directions: Blend cornstarch with cold water.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook and stir about 3 minutes.
Cool and serve over ice cream or cake.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.
If there are leftovers, store in refrigerator.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix crushed pineapple and instant pudding mix.
Stir until dissolved.
Add sour cream.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Put in refrigerator.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water, melt sherbet in gelatin mixture. Add fruit and nuts, pour mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter blossom cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together. Use rounded teaspoons. Roll into balls and roll in bowl of sugar. Place rounded balls on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove from oven and immediately press candy piece down in center of cookie. Remove from cookie sheet and cool.

title: frost and decorating frosting
directions: Beat all ingredients for 10 minutes (at least).

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Add all ingredients to macaroni.
Mix well.

title: the original cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for several hours to let flavors blend.
Serve with crackers and chips.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift flour and baking soda.
Cream sugar and sour cream; add eggs.
Beat until foamy.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lyndon b. johnson's barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter; add vinegar, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, lemon juice, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well and pour over meat.

title: spanish cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook until cabbage is tender.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla and milk.
Pour into buttered casserole and sprinkle with the following topping.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring to dissolve sugar well.
Add margarine or butter; keep heating until it melts.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, vanilla, oatmeal and coconut.
May add nuts if desired. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and cool.

title: cool fruit dip
directions: Blend together and chill for serving later (at least 6 hours). Cut up your favorite fruit and serve.

title: peanut butter twist
directions: Put the ingredients (except biscuits) into the pan you will be baking in.

title: angel food pie
directions: Better made day ahead of serving.
Mix together cornstarch and 3/4 cup sugar.
Pour on boiling water, little at a time, or it lumps.
Cook until thick and clear, stirring constantly.

title: "a lotta cookies"(at least 11 dozen oatmeal)
directions: Cream
sugar and butter (shortening).
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix	flour,	baking powder, nutmeg and salt together and add
alternating
with milk.
Last, add raisins, nuts and oatmeal. Will be dry and you may want to mix with your hands. Put
small amount
on	the ungreased cookie sheet, making the cookies the size you want.
(As the cooking goes on for quite a long
time, you
will
find
that you will be making larger cookies!!!)

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a well-greased casserole dish, except crackers and butter.
Crush enough crackers to make 1 cup and mix with butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Delicious served as side dish for poultry or pork.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onions; saute until golden, about 30 minutes.
Add broth, water, wine and Worcestershire. Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Place bread slices on baking sheet in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Pour soup into tureen. Place toast on top; sprinkle with both cheeses.
Dot with butter and heat in a 400° oven until cheese melts.
Serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chinese fried shrimp balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil.
Shape mixture into balls with a teaspoon.
Heat oil and deep fry shrimp balls until golden. Drain and serve immediately or keep warm in oven.
Good served with hot mustard or plum sauce.

title: pan buckeyes
directions: In a 2-quart glass bowl, put powdered sugar, 1 cup peanut butter and margarine.
Microwave 1 minute; mix.
Microwave 1 minute; mix.
Spread in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan lined with wax paper.
In the same bowl, put chocolate morsels and 1/2 cup peanut butter.
Microwave 1 minute; mix.
Microwave 1 minute; mix. Spread over first layer in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate and then lift out and cut into squares.

title: mango bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two loaf pans.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon into a small mixing bowl and set aside.
In a large bowl, combine eggs, oil and sugar. Combine with dry ingredients and blend well.
Fold mangos, raisins, nuts and coconut.
Pour into loaf pans and bake 45 to 60 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: sweet sour dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and cut in quarters, enough to fill 4 quart jars.
Add 3 or 4 slices of onions, 2 stalks celery and 2 pieces of dill.
Heat the sugar, salt, vinegar and water very hot and pour over pickles. Seal at once. Put in cool, dark place and let set 30 days, then eat.

title: mike's favorite strawberry dessert
directions: Use trifle bowl, a large glass bowl or a long pan.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Beat softened margarine.
Stir in sour cream.
Add biscuit mix and stir until dry ingredient is moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin pan and bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: cinnamon brownies
directions: Combine oleo, Crisco, cocoa and water and bring to a boil. Remove and add flour, sugar, sour milk and baking powder; beat well and add eggs, vanilla and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Add carrots and mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add vanilla. Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until lightly browned on bottom.
Frost with icing.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: (This recipe will double well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.)

title: crab dip
directions: Melt cream cheese and soup in nonstick frypan.
Stir until smooth.
Add gelatine; stir and let cool.
Add mayonnaise, crabmeat onion and celery.
Mix together and put in copper mold or desired mold/dish.
Chill at least 12 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: cheese potatoes casserole
directions: Put potatoes in casserole dish. Mix milk and flour. Pour over potatoes and onion.
Put grated cheese on top and bake at 350° until potatoes are done.

title: yeast doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in the water. Mix together milk, shortening, sugar, salt and then add eggs and flour.

title: dump cake
directions: In oblong cake pan, pour cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple and sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Sprinkle on dry cake mix.
Pour melted oleo on top.
Sprinkle with coconut and bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, flour and salt.
Add corn.
Put in dish and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chewy cake
directions: Melt margarine and sugar together over low heat in large pot. Add one egg at a time and beat until smooth and light.
Add pecans and flour one cup at a time.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a greased and floured (or vegetable sprayed) 10 x 14-inch pan at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 28 (2 x 2 1/2-inch) squares.
Don't overbake.
Makes a chewy, brownie-like goody.

title: fresh peach cake
directions: *Or use frozen sweetened peaches and reduce sugar to 1 cup.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla extract until creamy. Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in oats and butterscotch morsels.
Drop by tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes for chewier cookies, 9 to 10 minutes for crispier cookies.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: baked salmon cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray cookie sheet with nonstick vegetable cooking spray. Combine salmon, bread crumbs, green onion, egg, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce in medium size bowl.
Stir well.
Shape mixture into 4 equal patties.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake 5 to 8 minutes on each side or until golden and heated through.
High in protein, low in calories and fat and a good recipe if you're watching your cholesterol.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk; fold in Cool Whip.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 layer of graham crackers; add 1/2 pudding mix, 1 layer crackers, rest of pudding and top with graham crackers.
Top with frosting.
Chill overnight.

title: rice dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Some cut up celery and dried parsley flakes may be added.
Put in microwave and microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Take out and stir.
Microwave 10 more minutes.
Stir.
If drying, add some water and microwave 10 more minutes.

title: charlie's cheesecake
directions: Bring cream cheese to room temperature.
Preheat oven to 350°. Cream down cheese to eliminate lumps.
Add vanilla and salt.
Mix, scraping sides continuously.
Add sugar and mix.
Add egg yolks and mix.
Add whole eggs and mix.
Mixer should make small, soft peaks. If too stiff, add small amounts of egg yolk.
In a 10 x 2-inch spring-form pan, layer bottom with cracker crumbs.
Rub sides of pan with vegetable oil.
Add batter, shake gently to eliminate bubbles.
Bake until center is firm (45 to 55 minutes).
Cool. Remove from pan.
Freeze 24 hours before slicing or serving.

title: fudge sundae dessert
directions: Crush Oreos; save 1/3 cup crumbs and mix with 1 stick melted oleo.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add ice cream, softened.
After this layer, return to freezer until hard.
Boil remaining stick oleo, sugar, milk and unsweetened chocolate 10 to 15 minutes, stirring.
When cool, spread over ice cream; return to freezer until ready to serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given and bake in slow oven at 300 to 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour oil over Raisin Bran.
Sift all dry ingredients together. Beat eggs.
Add buttermilk to eggs.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Add Bran-oil mixture.
Refrigerate 48 hours before baking.
Bake in well-greased muffin tins or paper liners for 15 minutes at 350°.
Batter will keep 6 weeks.
(Can halve recipe.)

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix tomato paste, mustard and brown sugar.
Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients and 1/2 of tomato paste mixture.
Mix well.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Beat eggs until blended together; add milk, salt and pepper. Stir until mixed thoroughly.
Cut cheese into small chunks and add to mixture.
Cook macaroni until tender; add to mixture.
Add margarine.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes until brown.

title: easy stuffed peppers
directions: Slice stem ends from peppers; scoop out seeds.
Blanch in boiling water (2 to 3 minutes).
Drain well.
Season insides of peppers with salt and pepper.
Combine ground beef and next 6 ingredients.
Stuff peppers with meat mixture; place in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven.
Top peppers with cheese and dollop of chili sauce.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: egg custard
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook 35 or 40 minutes until done.
Stick a knife in center; if it comes out clean, it is done.

title: pittsburgh potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in salted water until tender; drain. Combine remaining ingredients and cook until thick.
Add potatoes. Bake at 350 for 35-40 minutes.

title: cheesy ham casserole
directions: Cube ham. Cook potatoes and cut up. Make white sauce with milk, butter, self-rising flour, salt and pepper. Add Cheddar cheese, onion flakes sauteed in butter and mustard. Fold in meat and potatoes. Put in 9 x 13 dish. Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: drop biscuits
