directions: Stir
together flour, baking powder and
salt.	Cut
in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Make a well in dry mixture; add milk all at once.	Stir
just
until dough clings together.	 Drop from tablespoon onto
greased
baking sheet. Bake at 450° for about 12 minutes.	Makes
to
14 biscuits.

title: marinated green beans
directions: Heat beans in own liquid.
When they are warm, drain and put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Heat bacon grease, sugar, mustard and vinegar; pour over the beans.
Crumble bacon over the top.
Serve at room temperature.
Serves 6.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs well. Add sugar, milk, flavoring and margarine. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Cook until firm at 350°.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons oleo in baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup brown sugar, pineapple and cherries.
Mix the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Pour 1/2 of cake batter in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
While cake cools, melt together margarine, caramels and condensed milk.
Pour over cooled cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and pecan pieces evenly over cake. Pour remaining batter over this and bake 20 minutes at 350°. When cake is cool, frost with Pepsi Icing.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake as directed on box.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Pour mixture over rhubarb and bake 60 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: waffles
directions: Measure dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Blend.
Combine egg yolks and milk. Stir into dry ingredients.
Stir in cooking oil. Carefully fold in egg whites and vanilla.
Do not overmix.
Pour 1/2 cup of batter onto preheated grid.
Close and bake.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, lemon juice and Eagle Brand. Fill pie crust and chill for 30 minutes. Serve.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Chop or coarse grind cabbage.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze out excess water.
Chop or coarse grind carrot and pepper.
Add to cabbage.
Boil the sugar, vinegar, water and spices.
Cool and pour over slaw mixture.

title: olive nut bread
directions: You will need a loaf pan.

title: tortilla chicken bake
directions: Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Chop tomatoes.
In skillet, add reserved liquid, onion, garlic, oregano and chili powder. Boil 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in tomatoes and chicken.
Cook until done, about 3 minutes.

title: health salad
directions: Blend cream and mayonnaise.
Add a little jello (which has been chilled) at a time until all is blended.
Add vegetables and stir well.
Refrigerate.

title: spud-slider
directions: In bowl, crumble (thawed) potato patties with fork.
Add onion, soup and sour cream.
Pour ingredients into glass pie dish. Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered. Makes 4 small servings, with a little leftover for the dog.
Can prepare and refrigerate the night before to be cooked the following day.

title: moist pineapple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in 1 bowl.
Mix thoroughly by hand. Pour into a 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix cheese, sugar and Cool Whip and pour in pretzel crust.
Dissolve jello and add strawberries.
Refrigerate until it begins to thicken.
Chill.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Into a flour sifter, put flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Sift into bowl.
Add milk, orange juice and egg. Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together.
Turn into greased, floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until straw or toothpick comes out clean.

title: best ever coleslaw
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
In saucepan, bring vinegar, sugar and salt to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Place in airtight bowl.
Will keep in refrigerator 3 to 4 weeks.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburg.
Add onion, pepper, tomatoes, tomato soup, salt, pepper and celery salt.
Simmer 4 to 5 hours.
Cook noodles and layer in casserole dish with sauce and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: fiesta turkey pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook ground turkey in a nonstick skillet. Stir in salsa.
Press crescent dough into bottom of a 9-inch greased pie plate and up sides to form a pie crust.
Spread turkey mixture evenly into crust.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: carrib breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage or bacon.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt and mustard.
In bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish, arrange bread cubes and top with sausage or bacon.
Sprinkle on cheese and pour egg mixture over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburg; drain and add Ragu.
Boil noodles.
Lay 3 to 4 noodles on bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put hamburg sauce on top, then layer cheeses.
Repeat two more times.
Cheese will be on top at the end.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° or 350°.
May cover loosely with foil.

title: baked beef and cabbage
directions: Have cabbage shredded coarsely to 5 or 6 cups full.
Spread half in large buttered casserole or roasting pan.
Heat oil in frypan and add beef, onion, rice, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir together but do not brown, about 10 minutes.
Spoon meat mixture over cabbage.
Top with remaining cabbage.
Heat tomatoes with water and bouillon cube to boiling and pour over all.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350° or until cabbage is tender.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in a greased and floured tube pan.
Very rich; needs no frosting.

title: artichoke-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; drain.
Spread casserole (1 1/2-quart) with mushrooms.
Drain artichokes.
Pour juice over mushrooms.
Line artichokes evenly in casserole.
Layer broccoli evenly over all.
Blend cream cheese, milk and butter until soft.
Spread over broccoli and add black pepper.
Blend Parmesan cheese with paprika and top casserole evenly. Refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Cook 30 minutes, covered, and 10 minutes, uncovered, at 350°.

title: cheese pie
directions: Eggs and cheese should be at room temperature.
Cream the cheese well; beat in 1/2 cup sugar.
Add eggs and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pie crusts (graham cracker premade); bake at 325° approximately 20 minutes or until set.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour on top of pies and return to oven for 5 minutes.
Cool and chill.

title: natalie's pork chops and rice
directions: Trim fat from pork chops; leave some fat in skillet and add some oil.
Brown the pork chops.
After browned, remove from skillet.
Add 1/2 cup of cooked rice to the skillet to get the flavor of the pork chops; drain excess fat from the skillet.
Add 8 ounce can of tomato sauce and 1/2 cup of water to the skillet. Add seasonings to taste.
Add chops to skillet.
Simmer until the chops are completely cooked.
Add another 8 ounce can of tomato sauce and a little water, if desired.

title: hawaiian grilled pork chops
directions: Drain pineapple; set aside 1/4 cup of juice.
Place chops in a shallow dish.
Combine pineapple juice, soy sauce, oil, onion, garlic and sugar; mix well.
Pour over chops.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Remove chops and place on grill.
Turn and baste with sauce frequently.
Place pineapple on each chop in the last few minutes of cooking time.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix together and let stand the cream of mushroom or chicken soup, mayonnaise, minced onions, diced chicken, chopped celery, salt, lemon juice and cooked rice.

title: garlic bread
directions: Cook together the last 5 ingredients until margarine melts. Slice bread diagonally 3/4 of the way through.
Pour mixture between slices and on top of loaf.
Wrap in aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix the sugar, milk, margarine or butter and cocoa in a pan. Place over medium heat and let boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and peanut butter.
Then add the oats.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper or nonstick pan.
Let cool for at least 30 minutes.

title: persimmon roll
directions: Can make as large amount as you want.

title: weight watchers pull-apart bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brush 1 teaspoon of margarine over bottom and sides of nonstick loaf pan. Spoon cheese into a small bowl. Cut biscuits into quarters. Dip biscuit pieces into remaining melted butter, then into cheese, turning lightly to coat. Layer coated biscuits into loaf pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Melt margarine in a 3-quart saucepan.
Add marshmallows over low heat, stirring constantly until marshmallows are melted. Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies and stir until well coated. Press warm mixture evenly and firmly in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan. Cut into squares when cool.

title: margaret's buttermilk salad
directions: Mix gelatin and pineapple (including juice) together. Bring to a boil to dissolve gelatin. Pour in dish and cool. Mix the buttermilk and Cool Whip together and spread over the gelatin. Cool.

title: art's e-z seafood salad
directions: Mix together; serve with Ritz crackers.
You can add 4 ounces cooked shrimp, cut up, for shrimp salad.
E-Z appetizing.
Low calorie.
Makes enough for 4 to 6 servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in long cake pan.
Cut in line squares. Put 1/2 of cake in punch bowl, then mix instant pudding as directed.
Put 1/2 pudding over cake, then 1 can fruit cocktail, juice and all.
Add 1 can of the cherry pie filling, rest of cake, pudding, fruit cocktail, then cherry pie filling.
Put it all in layers, then put the container of Cool Whip, coconut and nuts on top.
Put in refrigerator.

title: mini wraparounds
directions: Thaw pastry sheets at room temperature 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 400.
Mix egg and water.
Set aside.
Unfold pastry on lightly floured surface.
Roll each sheet into 12 inch squares and cut into 16 (3 inch) squares.
Place filling in center of each square.
Brush edges of squares with egg mixture.
Fold two opposite corners to center over filling.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden.
Makes 32 appetizers or mini desserts.

title: mushroom steak
directions: Trim fat from steak.
Cut in serving pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle soup mix over steak.
Pour mushrooms and liquid over soup mix.
Cover and bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.
If you prefer, you may cut steak in half and place in crock-pot.
Add soup mix and mushrooms and cook on high for 4 hours.
This will make enough broth to thicken for gravy if you wish.

title: broccoli, rice and cheese casserole
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: russian poppy seed cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and beat.
Pour batter in angel cake pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes. Turn out and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: creamed shepards pie
directions: 1. Brown ground beef.
Set aside. 2. In 12-inch non stick skillet heat 1 Tbsp. margarine until bubbly & hot.
Add carrots, mushrooms, onions, and saute stirring until onion is translucent. 3. Sprinkle broth mix and flour over vegetables and stir to combine.
Cook stirring constantly for minute.
Gradually stir in 1 c. milk and stirring constantly bringing to a boil.
Reduce heat and let simmer until mixture thickens. 4. Mix in ground beef, set aside.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine potatoes with remaining 1/2 c. milk, 1 Tbsp. margarine, mix till smooth. 5. Transfer meat mixture to greased casserole dish, spread whipped potatoes over meat.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake 10-15 minutes.
Then broil until potatoes are browned, 1-2 minutes.

title: sausage stuffing
directions: Over medium heat, fry together sausage, onion and celery until pork is browned and celery is tender. Stir in parsley. Salt and pepper to taste. Prepare stuffing mix as directed. Blend together stuffing and sausage mixtures.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add ice cubes.
Stir 3 to 5 minutes until jello begins to thicken.
Remove any remaining ice. Fold in Cool Whip, then oranges.
(Double or triple recipe if you bring it to a picnic or reunion.
It goes fast!)

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain mandarin oranges. Mix with all other ingredients. Refrigerate overnight to allow flavors to blend. One-fourth cup coarsely chopped pecans can be added, if desired. Good with ham or turkey.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Combine coconut, nuts, flour and margarine; press into bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes. Cool.
Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and chocolate, mixing until well blended.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into crust and chill several hours or overnight.
Garnish with additional toasted coconut.

title: never fail chocolate cake
directions: Add soda to milk.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift cocoa and flour together; add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and water.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: swedish heirloom cookies
directions: Cream shortening and butter; add gradually confectioners sugar.
Add salt, creaming well.
Add almonds.
Blend in flour gradually; mix thoroughly.
Add water and vanilla; mix thoroughly with fork.
Shape into balls or crescent rolls one even tablespoon of dough for each cookie.
Place on ungreased baking sheets flattened slightly.
Bake in moderate 325° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while still warm.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: In saucepan, bring pineapple to boil; stir in Jell-O until dissolved.
Take off stove.
When cool, fold in buttermilk, pecans and Cool Whip.
Pour in large oblong Pyrex pan.
Chill.

title: milky way cake
directions: Combine bars and 1/2 cup butter in saucepan; melt over low heat.
While candy is melting, prepare batter.
Cream 1/2 cup butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add flour and soda alternately with buttermilk, stirring until smooth.
Add candy mixture, beating well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into well greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Brown hamburger.
Cut onions, tomatoes and zucchini in 1/4 to 3/4-inch slices. In 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole, layer hamburger, onion, zucchini and tomatoes.
Sprinkle layer of oregano.
Repeat.
Top with grated cheese and bake for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: oven ribs
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Cut ribs into serving size pieces.
Place, meaty side down, in a large, shallow pan.

title: party pizza breads
directions: *May substitute seasonings with an Italian seasoning.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion, celery and peppers; cook until soft. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for about 30 minutes. Serve on soft rolls.

title: corned beef barbecue
directions: Cook celery in oil until tender, then add corned beef and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well. Add ketchup.
Makes 4 to 5 barbecues.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with milk to creamed mixture. Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 325° until done, 80 to 90 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: In mixing bowl, combine first 6 ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to dry ingredients and stir only until moistened.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square baking pan or a 10-inch heavy skillet.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut lettuce, onion and cauliflower into a large bowl.
Add crumbled bacon.
Mix sugar and Miracle Whip together; pour over all ingredients.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Let stand overnight. Mix before serving.
It can be served immediately or let stand overnight.

title: easy crock-pot supper
directions: Layer pork chops (uncooked) and stuffing, 2 layers of each. Pour boiling potatoes with about 2 cups of the potato water over mixture and cook on high for 4 hours or low all day.

title: ham b.b.q.  sauce
directions: Brown onions in butter.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add meat.

title: hearty garden vegetable soup
directions: Drain liquid from all vegetables except zucchini and tomatoes. Combine all ingredients in 5-quart soup pot and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer. This makes a very thick soup. Add more broth or tomatoes if you like more broth.

title: hunter style chicken
directions: Saute bacon in large skillet until partially cooked, then saute onion in same skillet until onion is tender. Remove bacon and onion.
Set aside.

title: fruit salad deluxe
directions: Into mixing bowl, put pineapple juice, Tang and dry instant pudding.
Mix well, then add fruit.
Chill and serve.

title: russian potato salad
directions: Cook frozen peas and carrots according to directions.
Dice potatoes, cucumbers, apples and chop up the hard-boiled eggs. Sprinkle with at least one tablespoon of salt and a pinch of pepper.
Blend sour cream and mayonnaise and add to mixture. Serve chilled, sprinkled with dill.
Leftover chicken or ham can be added for a well-balanced one-dish meal.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and form into a crust in a buttered pie pan.
Spoon cottage cheese over top of the spaghetti crust.

title: light orange cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over 1/2 cup orange juice in container of electric blender.
Heat remaining 1 cup orange juice to boiling and add to blender.
Cover and process at high speed until gelatin dissolves.
Stop blender, add orange rind, 1/2 cup sugar, salt, egg yolks, cottage cheese and vanilla.
Cover and process until smooth.
Pour into a large bowl; chill until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form, gradually beat in remaining 1/4 cup sugar and beat until stiff.
Fold into orange mixture.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over bottom of 8-inch spring-form pan; carefully spoon cheesecake filling over crumbs. Chill until firm.
Yields 16 servings, 100 calories per serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done (boil), debone chicken and save broth. Melt margarine and mix margarine with stuffing mix.
In casserole dish, put a layer of stuffing crumbs on bottom of dish; then a layer of chicken.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with 1 can of broth (saved from chicken) and pour over chicken.
Spread another layer of crumbs; and a layer of chicken; mix cream of chicken soup and 1 can chicken broth.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix all together and pour over chicken.
Lay pineapple and green pepper on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sun tea
directions: In a 2 quart clear glass container place tea bags.
Add 1 1/2 quarts
cold water; cover and let stand in full sun 2 to 3 hours or until of desired strength.
Remove tea bags.
Serve over ice. Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: one pan cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in the pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: orange delight salad
directions: Mix jello dry with cottage cheese.
Drain juice of pineapple and oranges.
Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: new year's eve punch
directions: Combine sugar with water and lemon juice; bring to boil for 1 minute.
Cool, add carbonated water and stir in lime, orange and grapefruit juice.
Pour into punch bowl over ice.
Add wine. Garnish with lemon slices and mint leaves, if desired.
Makes about 1 gallon.

title: deluxe lemon jello
directions: Dissolve lemon Jell-O in heated pineapple juice.
Blend cream cheese and coffee cream.
Add
cream
cheese
mixture to Jell-O, then add remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix oil, sugar and egg.
Stir in molasses.
Sift dry ingredients and add to the creamed mixture.
Chill dough.
Make small balls, dip in sugar and bake on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: salisbury steak - deluxe
directions: In a bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Blend well; set aside. In another bowl, lightly beat egg; add crumbs, onion, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup cream of mushroom soup and mix.
Add beef and mix well; shape into 6 patties.
In large skillet, brown patties in oil and drain.
Combine remaining soup with water; pour over patties. Cover and cook on low 10 to 15 minutes or until meat is done. Remove to dishes and pour sauce over; garnish with parsley.

title: applesauce apple butter(sugar-free)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender container and blend until smooth.
Pour mixture into a heavy saucepan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, with the lid ajar to allow steam to escape, for 20 minutes.
Allow to cool to room temperature and store covered in the refrigerator.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: corn puddin'
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients until well blended.
Melt butter in casserole dish.
Add corn to first mixture, then pour into dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Combine cream cheese, Good Seasons mix and mayo.
Spread on top of party rye bread.
Top with a thin slice of cucumber and sprinkle with fresh dill weed.

title: chicken boats
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix chicken, chili powder, sour cream and chicken soup.
Cook and stir potatoes in butter until golden.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pan and bake until toothpick comes out clean, about 1 hour.

title: sauerkraut slaw
directions: Rinse and drain kraut well. Combine with other ingredients. Cover and chill until ready to serve. Keeps well for 10 days or more.

title: dean's award winning divinity
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup and cook over medium heat until it forms a hard ball when dropped in cold water or spins a thread.
Pour syrup slowly into egg whites, beating constantly. Continue to beat until hardening begins.
Add vanilla and nuts. Pour into buttered pan and set until cold.

title: brown pot roast
directions: In Dutch oven, brown roast, then add the next 4 ingredients. Cook 1 1/2 hours, then add remaining ingredients.
Cook 1 1/2 hours more.
Serve with noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: creme de menthe bars
directions: Blend 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup sugar.
Stir in salt and vanilla, then eggs, flour and Hershey's syrup last.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: adobo
directions: Clean chicken and put it in a deep pot.
Mix soy sauce, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over chicken and cook at a slow simmer for 1/2 hour or until tender.

title: molasses cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add molasses and blend.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add the dry ingredients alternately with the milk.
Bake in a 375° oven for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water and add strawberries, pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Pour half of mixture into dish and congeal.
Spread sour cream on this layer.
Spread the remaining mixture on top of sour cream and place in refrigerator.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Separate dough into 8 triangles and flatten each slightly. Place about 2 teaspoons cheese, 1 teaspoon barbecue sauce and 1 chicken chunk on shortest side of each triangle.
Fold 2 corners over chicken chunk; roll to opposite point.
Pinch edges to seal. Place point side down on greased cookie sheet.
Brush with egg; sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 12 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.

title: caramel oatmeal chewies
directions: Mix together oats, 1 1/2 cups flour, brown sugar, soda and salt.
Stir in margarine; reserve 1 cup.
Press remaining into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes; top with chopped nuts and chocolate bits.
Mix caramel topping with 1 1/4 cups flour until smooth.
Drizzle over chocolate pieces to within 1/4-inch (important) of pan edge.
Sprinkle with reserved oat mixture.
Bake an additional 18 to 22 minutes; cool. Chill until set.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean and remove stems from mushrooms.
Mix thoroughly the bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, butter, garlic, onion, salt and pepper. Fill mushroom caps.

title: delight in a pan
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° until good and brown.
Cool completely.

title: southern sweet potato pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour and sugar.
Add potatoes, eggs, corn syrup, cinnamon, salt, oleo and milk.
Beat well and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: marshmallow nut fudge
directions: Butter an 8-inch baking pan.
In a small saucepan over medium heat, heat sugar, undiluted milk, butter or margarine and salt to boiling.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Beat vigorously until marshmallows melt.
Pour into pan; sprinkle with more chopped nuts, if desired. Cool in pan on a wire rack; cut into small squares.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce(microwave)
directions: Place ground beef, onion and garlic in a 2-quart casserole. Cover with waxed paper; microwave on High (100%) for 6 to 8 minutes or until meat is pink in center.
Stir halfway through cooking. Drain off excess grease.
Stir in tomato sauce, tomato paste and seasonings.
Microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Stir halfway through cooking.
Microwave on Low (30%) for 10 minutes to blend flavors.
Stir in spaghetti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: oven-fried hawaiian chicken
directions: Put chicken in large bowl.
Combine soy sauce, onion and ginger.
Pour over chicken.
Let marinate 2 hours, turning to coat all sides.
Drain; reserve the marinade.
Coat each piece with cornstarch.
In a shallow baking pan, heat butter; add chicken (skin side down).
Bake in a 425° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken; pour the combined pineapple with syrup, lemon juice and reserved marinade over chicken.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes more, basting.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip (1 cup) together; mix well, spread on top of 1st layer.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into balls and bake on am ungreased baking sheet at 400 degrees for 10-12 minutes.

title: english muffin loaves
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Heat liquids to 120°.
Add to dry ingredients.
Spoon into 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2) pans, greased and sprinkled with cornmeal.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place for 45 minutes.
Microwave on High 6 1/2 minutes.	Let rest 5 minutes. Turn out to cool.
When cool, I slice and store in freezer bag in freezer.
Take out slices as you want.
Makes great toast.

title: sky biscuits
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Cut in butter until coarse.
Add egg and milk; stir briefly.
Knead on floured surface.
Roll or pat to 1 inch thick.
Cut into biscuits.
Place in greased pan.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream cheese and butter; add egg and other ingredients. Add cake mix in
equal
parts.
Drop
by spoonful on cookie sheet. Bake in
moderate
oven until golden brown, about 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Eat and enjoy.

title: sweet potato cheesecake
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar, beat until smooth.
Blend in sweet potatoes and spices.
Add egg, beat well.
Pour into pie shell, bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: cherry pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar, Crisco and eggs (one at a time).

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes in an 8 x 12-inch ungreased pan.
Combine cream cheese and Cool Whip; spread over cooled crust.
Combine the last 2 ingredients; spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with a layer of Cool Whip; sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: hot mexican corn bread
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients. Top with Cheddar cheese and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Ready to serve.

title: biscuit crust for meat pies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg together.
Cut in Crisco until mixture looks like coarse meal.
Combine egg, water and lemon juice.
Add to flour mixture, mixing lightly with a fork until soft dough is formed.
Knead lightly on floured board about 20 seconds.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thick and cut into desired shape.
Place on top of pot pie filling.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 30 minutes or until browned and done.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter pan.
Layer whole graham crackers in pan.
Mix pudding and milk together.
Fold in vanilla and Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over graham crackers.
Put another layer of graham crackers, then the remaining pudding, Cool Whip mixture, then another layer of graham crackers.
Refrigerate 2 hours, then ice.

title: gingered chicken and almond stir-fry
directions: Combine soy sauce and 1 teaspoon cornstarch in medium bowl. Cut boneless, skinless chicken breasts into 1/4 x 1/4 x 2-inch strips and add to sauce.
Stir to coat.
Refrigerate 30 minutes. Combine water and bouillon granules in small bowl.
Stir until dissolved.
Add 2 teaspoons cornstarch and ginger.
Stir.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil to 365° in electric skillet.
Add broccoli, onion, garlic and bell pepper.
Stir-fry until crisp-tender.
Remove from skillet to serving dish with slotted spoon.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in same skillet at 365°.
Add chicken mixture and crushed red pepper.
Stir-fry until chicken is no longer pink.
Return vegetables to skillet.
Add bouillon mixture.
Stir until thickened.
Stir in nuts.
Serve with rice.

title: chow-chow
directions: Soak dried beans overnight and cook next morning, not over-soft, about 20 minutes.
Salt lightly.
Cook each vegetable until soft.
Mix together and put into jars.
Add syrup, which has been brought to a boil.
Cold pack 10 minutes in a cold water bath.

title: chicken chip casserole
directions: Boil celery and onion until tender.
Mix chicken, cream of chicken soup, celery and onion mixture, eggs, mayonnaise and 1 cup potato chips.
Put remaining chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cheese cake
directions: In a spring-form cake pan make crust of graham crackers, walnuts and melted margarine.
In a large bowl, mix cream cheese, eggs, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust and bake 50 to 55 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Roll crackers fine and add 2 tablespoons sugar, cinnamon and butter.
Line a 10-inch spring-form or other cake pan with removable bottom.

title: orange mincemeat salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add pineapple and break mincemeat in small pieces.
Add nuts.
Let set in refrigerator about 2 hours.
Great with any kind of meat.

title: super lima beans (just for melina)
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; remove from skillet, crumble and set aside.
Saute onions in bacon drippings until tender; add beans, soup and bacon, mixing well.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine butter and bread crumbs; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt butter in large saucepan and add cocoa; remove from heat.
Mix in sugar, eggs and vanilla; stir.
Stir in remaining ingredients; spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brownies pull away from pan.
Do not overbake.

title: old fashion buttermilk pie
directions: Mix milk, sugar, flour, flavoring and eggs well. Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Top with margarine, sliced into pieces.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: amazing ambrosia pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, butter and vanilla in electric blender container.
Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup coconut over bottom of two 8-inch pie pans that have been greased with margarine.
Pour half of mixture into each pan and allow to sit about 5 minutes, then sprinkle 1/2 cup coconut over top of each pie.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.
Store leftover pie in refrigerator.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Pour into oiled and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender, reserving 1/2 cup of liquid. Saute celery, onions and water chestnuts in three tablespoons of butter.
Mix vegetables in reserved liquid, onion, celery, water chestnuts, mayonnaise and cheese.

title: easy refrigerator rolls
directions: Stir ingredients together in order given.
Refrigerate dough at least 12 hours.
Form into rolls and let raise 2 hours before baking.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 36 rolls.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Gradually add all the other ingredients, but only adding 1/2 of nuts.
Mix together and chill well.
Form into a ball and roll in the remaining nuts.
Chill until served.

title: fried venison
directions: Trim all sinue from meat and tenderize with tenderizing hammer.
Marinate at least 2 hours, overnight is best.
Drain and dust with flour mixed with salt, lemon pepper and cayenne.
Deep fry but don't overcook.
Serve with cream gravy liberally seasoned with white and black pepper.

title: chicken
directions: First you go and buy the chicken.
Then go home and crack the eggs open.
You put it in that crumb stuff.
Shake it in crumb stuff.
Put it on the stove then take it off the stove.
You cut it and eat it.

title: t.j. miracle soup
directions: Mix all vegetables and cover with water in large pot.
Add onion soup mix, garlic and bouillon (dissolved in hot water).
If you don't like chicken or beef bouillon, you don't have to use it. Add fresh or minced garlic and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until vegetables are tender.

title: delicious chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in bowl.
Add remaining and blend well. Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes (greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan).
Frost with chocolate icing.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Cook until done.
Drain.
Put in casserole dish; add cream of celery soup, milk, cheese, sweet pepper and onion.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine, powdered sugar and vanilla together.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on wax paper and refrigerate 50 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Mix together beef, rice, egg, onion, tomato sauce and salt and pepper to taste. Wash and clean peppers out. Fill peppers with mixture. Place in baking dish. Pour undiluted tomato soup over peppers. Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chicken divan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place broccoli in bottom of 1 1/2-quart baking dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Evenly place chicken on top.
Melt margarine in a saucepan.
Stir in flour until mixed.
Add skim milk and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Add remaining ingredients except bread.
Pour over chicken.
Break bread into pieces and put on top.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: blueberry crumble pie
directions: Pour berries into pie shell, mix sugar, sour cream and flour; pour over berries.
Mix Ritz cracker crumbs, sugar and butter; crumble over pie.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Sift together next 4 ingredients.
Mix all these together and add melted shortening. Pour 1/2 to 3/4 full into muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon and vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set. Top with strawberries and desired amount of glaze.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: lemon squares
directions: Pour over crust.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk in pan. Add butter and cook on medium heat until mixture comes to a boil. Remove from heat and cool 1 minute. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar and corn syrup; cook over low heat, stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Add eggs, vanilla and salt; blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell (9-inches, deep) and top with pecans.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: fudge brownies(low calorie)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 8-inch square baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In medium-size bowl, stir together sugar, Sweet One, margarine, eggs, Butter Buds Sprinkles and vanilla.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine
sugar,
corn
syrup
and
water; cook over low heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cook to soft ball stage or
thermometer,
stirring constantly.
Add salt and peanuts; cook to hard crack stage or 295°.
Remove from heat; add
butter and soda.
Stir lightly.
Pour into greased waxed paper.
Cool partially lifting around edges with knife.
Cool until firm. Turn.
Cool completely.
Break into pieces.

title: lemon squares
directions: Work first 3 ingredients like pastry and press mixture into the bottom of an 8-inch square pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°. While this is baking, combine the next 6 ingredients.
Pour lemon mixture on top of baked pastry and return to oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
The shorter time will give a soft, moist result, the longer time a drier, crispier square.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix together all ingredients and bake for 45 minutes.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Place in 1 bowl. Mix and drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until light brown around edges, about 8 minutes. Can decorate with raisins or colored sugar.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, cocoa and salt in mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sliced cucumber pickles
directions: Pour over cukes and onions.
Mix well.
Nothing soaked or boiled.
Place in jars and put in refrigerator.
Keeps about 6 months in sealed jars.

title: microwave creamy hot bacon dressing
directions: Microwave bacon in microwave-safe pie plate, covered with paper towel, on High 3 to 4 minutes, stirring once or twice until crisp.
Remove bacon bits to another paper towel-lined microwave plate or paper plate.
Reserve 3 tablespoons drippings.

title: taco salad
directions: Chop tomatoes and place in bottom of large bowl.
Chop lettuce and put on top of tomatoes.
Grate cheese and place on top of lettuce.
Don't mix together until end.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Fry hamburger; then add beans and cook until hot clear through.
Break up chips in salad; then add beans and hamburger. Toss well and serve immediately.
Makes lots!

title: mashed potato doughnuts
directions: Sift
together
flour,
baking powder, salt, nutmeg and sugar. Add eggs, butter, sweet milk and mashed potatoes.
Fry in hot fat.
Makes 36 donuts.

title: divinity
directions: Mix and boil sugar, syrup, hot water and salt. Cook until syrup reaches hard ball stage on candy thermometer. Pour slowly into egg whites while beating. Add pecans. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: polish hunter's stew (bigos)
directions: Rinse the sauerkraut with cold water. Drain well. In a large stockpot, combine the sauerkraut, ham or pork, bay leaves, mushrooms, peppercorns, allspice and salt. Add 6 c. broth, bouillon or water. Cook uncovered for 15 minutes over medium heat. Cover and simmer over low heat for 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour spicy slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, carrots, sweet peppers and onions.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Combine remaining ingredients for dressing.
Pour over slaw mixture and toss lightly.
Cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours, tossing occasionally.
Yields 10 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: ground turkey surprise
directions: Brown turkey, may need to add a little oil.
Will not have much grease if any.
Slice onions and peppers.
Add to meat then add mushrooms and sauce.
Cook until vegetables are tender, about 1 hour.
Use frying pan or electric frying pan.

title: spinach-eggplant lasagna
directions: Peel eggplant and cut it into 1/4-inch rounds.
Thaw and squeeze dry the spinach.
Cook, drain and cool the noodles.
Have a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish ready to use.
Coat a nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Cook eggplant in batches over medium heat 4 minutes per side.
Mix spinach, Ricotta and cottage cheese, 1/2 cup of Parmesan cheese and eggs until blended.
Heat oven to 350°.
Spread 1 cup spaghetti sauce evenly over bottom of baking dish.
Place 3 noodles lengthwise on top.
Cover with half spinach mixture, half eggplant and 5 slices Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat second layer.
Top with remaining noodles, overlapping to cover, then remaining sauce and Mozzarella.
Sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons Parmesan.
Bake 1 hour or until bubbling and light brown around edges.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.
Makes 12 pieces.

title: olde english raisin pie
directions: Cook slowly until thickened.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Make meringue with 3 egg whites and 6 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 325° for about 10 minutes (until peaks are light brown).

title: pecan logs
directions: Mix marshmallow cream, confectioners sugar and vanilla together.
Roll out long and thin (about as big as your thumb), about 8 to 10-inches.
Freeze overnight.
Melt the caramel candies, butter and evaporated milk in double boiler.
Chop pecans and spread on waxed paper.
Take the frozen rolls and dip in caramel, then roll in pecans.
Put back in freezer or refrigerator.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt until mixture resembles fine crumbs. Combine egg (slightly beaten), vinegar and water. Sprinkle over dry ingredients. Mix with fork. Let stand 10 minutes. Roll out. This recipe makes 2 (9-inch) crust pies and 1 (9-inch) pie shell. Very good for freezing. Bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes.

title: veggie bars
directions: Lightly grease 10 inch x 15 inch jelly roll pan.
Spread out dough and pat down in pan.	Bake 7 to 8 minutes at 350° until brown. Cool. Mix salad dressing, cream cheese and dry ranch dressing. Spread over cooled dough.
Sprinkle veggies over and press down into cream cheese. Sprinkle with sharp cheese.
Chill 2 hours. Cut into small squares.
Serve cold.
Very tasty.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts (season to taste with salt, pepper, garlic and onion salt).
Take chicken breasts and tear into bite sizes; set aside.
Take 13 x 9-inch casserole dish and crush 1 bag tortilla chips into bottom of dish.
Place chicken pieces on top of chips.
Cut onion tails and sprinkle on top.
Mix the 2 soups together and pour on top of this.
Add cheese slices across top, then pour Ro-Tel tomatoes on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Melt cheese.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and soda together.
Add pineapple, eggs and vanilla. Beat well.
Pour into a greased sheet cake pan. Add nuts separately on top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh peach-squash casserole
directions: Wash and slice squash.
Place layer of squash then layer of fresh peaches in a two-quart casserole.
Continue alternating layers of fruit and vegetable until all have been used.
Sprinkle brown sugar and salt over the combination and dot with butter. Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes to an hour.
Serves four.

title: baked apple in a skillet
directions: Place in a large skillet, sugar, apple juice, margarine and cinnamon.
Melt, then add apples.
Cover and cook until tender.

title: cherry pizza cake
directions: Butter Pyrex baking dish or sheet cake pan.
Pour the cherry pie filling into the dish and sift the white cake mix over this. Melt margarine and pour over the cherries and cake mix.
Sprinkle the nuts over the top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apricot shake
directions: Put ingredients in blender. Cover and blend until smooth.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Add and mix soup, salt, pepper and water with rice, celery and onion.
Make layers of rice mixture and broccoli.
Top with melted cheese or grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in an 8-inch square pan.
Serves 4.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flour and egg yolks.
Mix well. Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie crust. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until set.
Remove from oven and top with meringue; return to oven and brown to your desire.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put cucumbers in cold water until crisp.
Wipe dry and slice. Add onion slices and salt.
Let it sit for 1 hour.
Add 1-quart vinegar and a little water, sugar, mustard seed, ginger root and celery seed.
Boil all together for 5 minutes.
Can while they are hot.

title: dinner pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients as you would regular pancakes.
Fry in a skillet, just as you would regular pancakes.
(Best if fried in butter.)
Serve with chicken gravy and watch your family's surprise.

title: german apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and salad oil until foamy.
Add sugar, flour, cinnamon, vanilla, soda and salt; mix well.
Add diced apples and nut meats.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: beef potato bake
directions: In shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish, combine potatoes, oil and pepper.
Firmly press mixture across bottom of pan and up sides of dish to form a shell.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes. In skillet, brown ground beef.
Drain and stir in gravy mix, water and garlic salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add mixed vegetables; reduce heat to medium and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can of onions.
Place in potato shell.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix undrained pineapple and sour cream.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over pineapple and mix well.
When it begins to thicken, pour into crust and refrigerate.
When set, top with Cool Whip and nuts.

title: coconut logs
directions: Combine and cook for 10 minutes the dates, eggs, sugar and oleo, then add Rice Krispies, graham cracker crumbs and nuts. Cool.
Shape into a log and roll in coconut.
Chill and slice or shape into individual logs and roll in coconut.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and press into a buttered spring-form pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool slightly.
Beat only egg yolks until bubbly.
Add softened cream cheese and mix on low until blended.
Add sour cream; mix well.
Gradually add sugar and mix until dissolved.
Add vanilla.
In a separate bowl beat egg whites until very stiff; add to cheese mixture.
Mix on low.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, then reduce to 275° for 15 minutes.
Cool; cover.
Refrigerate overnight (approximately 8 hours).
The top should be a very dark golden brown and may crack (this is normal).

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Put dry ingredients in mixing bowl. Boil together margarine, cocoa and water.
Cool slightly and pour over dry mixture.
Beat well, then add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Beat a little.
Pour onto large cookie sheet, greased and floured.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: baked squash casserole
directions: Slice onion and squash; cook until tender (about 12 to 14 minutes in the microwave).
Drain well.
Mash and add margarine. Stir until it melts.
Add toast cubes, milk, salt, sugar and beaten eggs.
Mix well; turn into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Can also be microwaved for about 20 minutes. Serves 4.
Double recipe to serve a larger crowd.

title: broccoli salad 1
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Put in large casserole dish.
Melt 1 stick margarine.
Crush 2 packages Ritz crackers and mix with margarine.
Sprinkle over other ingredients in dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swedish yellow brownies
directions: Dump all ingredients in a bowl; mix it up.
Dump in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and sugar, if desired.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix sugar, flour, soda and salt.
Add eggs, cooking oil and buttermilk.
Mix ingredients well with electric mixer.
Hand stir in Raisin Bran.
Fill muffin pan and bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Remainder of mixture can be stored in refrigerator in covered container.

title: wayne's favorite squash lasagna
directions: Cook together the beef, onion and green pepper until browned; drain.
Add basil, oregano, tomato sauce and rice.
Boil thick sliced pieces of squash.
Mix the egg into the cottage cheese. Put meat mixture on top of squash, then put cottage cheese mixture over that and layer.
Put grated cheese on top of it all.
Cook for 45 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: red bean and sausage stew
directions: Prepare beans for cooking according to the master recipe.
In Dutch oven or sauce pot, combine beans with about 5 cups fresh water.
Bring to boil; reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer beans 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Mix everything well and pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 275° for 50 minutes.

title: spicy chocolate cake
directions: Dissolve chocolate and instant coffee in the boiling water; set aside.
Mix raisins and walnuts with the 1 1/2 teaspoons flour; set aside.
Cream butter and brown sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat thoroughly.
Add chocolate mixture.
Sift flour with salt, soda and spices; add in thirds, alternately with sour cream, beating until smooth after each addition.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Turn into a 10-cup greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake at 325° in preheated oven for 50 minutes.

title: virginia ham pate
directions: Mix and spread on tiny biscuits.
Serve warm.
May add cheese and/or poppy seed to vary.
Or, the ham mixture may be rolled into small balls (1 teaspoon) with a nut inside, then rolled in fine bread crumbs and quickly deep fat fry until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: upside down pizza
directions: Brown ground beef and onions, drain. Add spaghetti sauce mix and tomato sauce. Simmer gently to let flavors combine. Spread meat mixture in 9 X 13 pan. Layer on mozzarella cheese and sour cream. Top with crescent rolls, brush with butter and sprinkle on parmesan cheese. Bake at 375°for 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour, chips and vanilla.
Drop by heaping tablespoonful onto cookie sheet.
Press with a fork until round; they should be pretty thick.
Put pecan halve on top, if desired.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12-15 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Melt butter.
Saute onions and cabbage for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with flour.
Add water gradually and heat to boiling. Add all other ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: toombs county, georgia, fruitcake cookies
directions: Mix batter ingredients.
Pour over diced fruits and nuts; mix. Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake for about 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool on rack, then store in tight container several days (a week or more).
This batter is so stiff I mix the fruit and nuts in with more of a kneading than a mixing motion.

title: creamy horseradish dip
directions: *You may substitute 4 crispy bacon slices (crumbled) for the ham.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar and butter.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift 2 cups flour, salt, cinnamon and soda together and add to first mixture. Mix 1/2 cup flour with chopped dates, candied cherries, candied pineapple and nuts.
Mix well.
Add more flour, if needed, for stiff dough.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: coffee breakers(sweet roll)
directions: Melt butter; stir in sugar and syrup.
Heat to boiling. Spread in jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch.
Sprinkle with pecans.
In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; add baking mix and beat vigorously.
Turn dough on floured board and knead 10 minutes.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Freezes great! Add nuts (optional).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Cut chicken up into small pieces. Combine both cans of soup with broth and onion in saucepan until onion is tender.
Put half of the stuffing mixture on the bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish.
Place all of the chicken on top of the stuffing.
Pour the soup mixture over the chicken.
Place the remaining half of the stuffing mixture on top.
Cut margarine in little pats and put on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until very brown on top.

title: white chocolate cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine wafer crumbs, butter and 1/4 cup of the sugar.
Press evenly into the bottom and 1-inch up the sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Refrigerate.

title: longevity minestrone
directions: Heat oil in large pot.
Add garlic and onion; saute until soft.
Add carrots, celery, cabbage, spinach and broccoli.
Add basil, oregano, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Cover and cook on low heat for 10 minutes.
Add red peppers, beans, tomatoes and water. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Bring to boil.
Add pasta; cook 10 to 15 minutes, until tender.
Serve topped with 1 tablespoon cheese.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Put potatoes through medium blade of food chopper or chop in blender (if you like, chop 1 small onion along with them).
Add salt, pepper, flour and egg.

Beat with spoon until well blended. Drop large spoonfuls onto hot, well oiled skillet or griddle. Cook until bottom is browned, then turn and brown the other side. A traditional accompaniment for pot roast.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate chip jello cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine sugar (white and brown), butter, vanilla and pudding mix in large mixer bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in chips and nuts.
(Batter will be stiff.)
Drop by rounded spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: granola
directions: Pour honey and melted butter over dry ingredients.
Mix well. Bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.
Stir; then bake for 10 more minutes.
Cool completely.
Store in sealed container.

title: amy's strawberry birthday cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and line the bottom of a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan (it looks like a cookie sheet with sides) with waxed paper.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a small bowl.
With electric mixer at high speed, beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add 1/3 cup granulated sugar, one tablespoon at a time, and continue beating until stiff peaks form.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Break tortillas into small pieces in the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown the ground beef; mix all the ingredients together except the cheese and pour it over the tortillas.
Sprinkle cheese on top of meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: green jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple and add enough water to juice to make 2 cups. Heat to a boil, add jello and dissolve well.
Put in refrigerator until it starts to jell.
Add salt, cheese, mayonnaise, pineapple and nuts.
Put back in refrigerator until it jells good.

title: tangy russian tea
directions: Combine ingredients and sift.
Use 2 teaspoons per cup and pour in boiling water.
(If you use it all at once, this will make 2 quarts of tea.)

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients together and chill at least 2 hours. Serve with crackers or chips.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Stir the pudding and crushed pineapple together for several minutes until it thickens. Drain the fruit cocktail. Add the fruit, nuts and marshmallows to the pudding. Mix in the cool whip. Chill 2 hours or more.

title: belgian waterzooie chicken
directions: Rub chicken and cavity with lemon, salt, pepper and thyme. Melt butter and add veggies.
Stir and simmer.
Add chicken, bouillon and wine; boil until veggies are tender.
In a serving dish, put yolk, cream, juice and chicken.
Serve immediately. Serve with white rice.
Waterzooie is even better prepared one day in advance of serving.

title: jumbo apple dumplings(6 servings)
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the flour, baking powder and salt. Using a pastry blender, cut in the shortening until it is about the size of small peas.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of the milk over a part of the mixture; gently toss with a fork.
Push to side of bowl. Repeat until all is moistened.
Divide into 6 equal portions.
Form each into a ball; cover and set aside.
On a lightly floured surface, roll out each portion of dough into a 7 1/2 to 8-inch circle, trimming uneven edges.
Place an apple in the center of each circle of dough.

title: wakefield peanut and felts ham spread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put in blender and blend until smooth all ingredients.
Stuff fresh mushroom caps with the spread and bake 15 minutes.
You can
use this as a spread for party sandwiches or on crackers.
It also makes a delicious dip for vegetables; just add more sour cream to obtain a dip consistency and add more onion to suit taste.

title: heavenly haddock
directions: Put fish in baking dish.
Cover with butter, salt and pepper. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix soup and sour cream together. Cover fish with this mixture. Return to oven and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: texas-style brisket
directions: Mix last 7 ingredients together and marinate brisket (that has been well trimmed) in a tightly covered pan for 12 hours in refrigerator.
Cook in 250° to 275° oven in tightly foil-covered pan for 2 to 3 hours.

title: peach pie
directions: Pat into pan.
Prick and bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: pat's blueberry french toast
directions: Cut bread into 1-inch cubes; place half in a greased 9 x 13 x 2 baking dish. Cut cream cheese into 1/2-inch cubes and place over bread. Top with blueberries and remaining bread.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: oatmeal cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Wash cookie sheet each time.

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: Boil green beans, limas, and peas together.
(Don't overcook.) Drain.
Add eggs, onion, salad oil, mayonnaise, and Worcestershire sauce.
Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: cinnamon dandies
directions: Cream the butter.
Add powdered sugar and salt.
Add applesauce and vanilla.
Blend in flour.
Place on ungreased sheet in balls.
Flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Roll warm cookies in cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: homemade lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dry ingredients for bottom layer; cook for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Combine eggs, lemon juice and almond extract; pour over bottom layer.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; while warm, sprinkle with 3 tablespoons of confectioners sugar.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Use a 9-inch square pan.

title: cracker pudding
directions: Put first

5 ingredients all together and cook until thick. Put in dish and cool. Mix instant pudding with milk. Spread on top of first layer, then spread this layer with Cool Whip. Spread coconut on top of Cool Whip.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake slowly for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana salad
directions: Slice bananas into a bowl and set aside.
In a saucepan melt butter, add sugar and milk.
Boil until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add peanut butter, stirring while boiling, remove from heat when it thickens.
Pour mixture over the bananas.

title: impossible tuna pie
directions: Preheat
oven
Grease pie plate 10-inch.
Mix tuna, cheeses,
onions
and
pimientos
in
pie
plate.
Beat remaining ingredients 15 seconds in blender.
Pour into plate. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serve with sliced tomatoes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix chicken soup, chilli peppers and sour cream until smooth. Add about 2 to 3 ounces cheese.
Mix well.
Place 2 to 3 tablespoons chicken on medium-size flour tortilla shell.
Put 2 to 3 tablespoons soup mixture on top. Fold up tortilla shell.
Put in greased baking dish and cover with the rest of the soup mixture. Grate rest of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: "no bakes"(no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies)
directions: Butter oblong cake pan and set aside.
In large bowl, combine oatmeal, coconut, raisins and walnuts; set aside.
In heavy saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Stir until dissolved and margarine is melted.
Bring to a boil and boil for just one minute.
Remove from heat and quickly add vanilla and peanut butter; stir until melted.
Add ingredients from bowl and stir together.
Pour mixture into buttered pan and let cool.
Cut into squares.
Keep refrigerated.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Fold in blueberries.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: no-knead french bread
directions: Beat the above ingredients until well mixed and add: 1 cup flour.
Beat with mixer for 2 minutes and add:
1 c. flour.
Mix with spoon until it is a soft, but not too sticky dough (add up to another 1/2 c. flour if necessary).
Butter a warm bowl, put dough in it; cover bowl tightly with saran wrap and let rise 45 minutes. Punch down dough and shape into French loaf and place on greased, cornmeal sprinkled cookie sheet.
Let rise again until doubled (about 30 min.), cut diagonal slices across the top and bake at 400 degrees for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: flank steak teriyaki
directions: Mix all ingredients except steaks.
Marinate steaks for at least 2 hours (better if longer).
Grill steaks.
Yields: 4 to 6 servings.

title: nectar fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Sprinkle with finely chopped filberts and chill.

title: pork chop monterey
directions: Put a slice of onion on each piece of meat.
Mix remaining ingredients well.
Pour over meat and onion.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.

title: coonhunters cake
directions: Combine all ingredients with wooden spoon until well blended. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Prick cake with fork after baking and ice cake while hot.

title: rolls
directions: Mix and drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread 1 stick melted butter and 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder over biscuits.

title: true blue cheese dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir, cover and chill a least 30 minutes.

title: eggless-fruitless fruit cake
directions: Place shortening and sugar in mixing bowl and beat until fluffy; set aside.	Mix flour, salt, cloves, cinnamon, nutmeg and cocoa and set aside.
Stir baking soda into buttermilk and add alternately with the flour mixture to shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla, walnuts and dates (dates make the cake a little moist). Bake in a greased and floured funnel pan in a preheated 350° oven about 1 hour.
Test with toothpick.
Serve wedges with real whipped cream, preferably, or vanilla ice cream.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Thaw berries, drain and save juice. Drain pineapple; save juice.
Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add saved juices; should be about 1 cup.
If not, add water to make 1 cup.
Add fruit and nuts.
Put half the mixture into clear glass container and chill until set.
Keep rest of mixture at room temperature.
When first half is set, spread with sour cream.
Carefully pour remaining jello over top.
Chill until completely set.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Coarsely chop artichoke hearts.
In small bowl, combine cheese, mayonnaise and half and half.
Mix well. Stir in bell pepper, pimento and artichoke hearts.
Spoon mixture into shallow baking dish and bake for 25 minutes.
Serve warm with Melba toast.
Serves 6.

title: summer spaghetti(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Peel and dice the tomatoes.
Add the onion, garlic, parsley, basil and olive oil to the tomatoes; season with taste with vinegar, salt and peppers.
Set aside.
Boil the spaghetti until al dente and drain.
Toss the hot spaghetti with the tomato mixture.
Serve immediately, topped with cheese.
The tomato mixture may be prepared ahead, but if it is refrigerated, bring it back to room temperature before mixing with the hot spaghetti.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients in blender until smooth.
Put clove of garlic in jar.
Makes 3 cups.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients with enough milk to hold together. Make into meat balls and place in baking dish.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over the meat balls.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
If meat balls begin to get too brown, cover with foil.

title: white house supper
directions: Open all cans.
Brown garlic in the olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Be careful not to burn garlic.
Once garlic is brown, add dried basil and brown it for no more than 10 seconds, then quickly add crushed tomatoes and juice from cans of clams, reserving clams for later.
Lower heat to slow simmer. Cook for 2 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: clam dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth; add drained clams, garlic powder, parsley flakes, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.

title: sausage breakfast squares
directions: Place 6 slices of bread, buttered side down on bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan. Top with sausage, then cheese. Place remaining 6 slices of bread, buttered side up, on top of cheese. Beat eggs and "half and half" together and pour over ingredients. Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Let set 30 minutes before serving. Cut into squares. Enjoy!

title: zucchini preserves
directions: Mix zucchini and sugar together well and boil for 6 minutes. Add pineapple and lemon juice and boil for 10 minutes.

title: quick punch
directions: Heat together until it makes a syrup.
Add enough water to make 2 gallons.

title: pizza bread
directions: Let dough rise.
Roll out dough on floured board.
Mix together egg, grated cheese and parsley.
Brush mixture on top of dough.
Layer American cheese and pepperoni on top of mixture. Roll layered dough like a log.
Bake on a cookie sheet for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet and sour turkey legs
directions: Brown turkey under broiler in a pan until skin is crisp. Sprinkle with garlic.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over turkey.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Baste occasionally.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Combine in blender. Store in refrigerator.

title: sunshine punch
directions: Empty lemonade mix into large punch bowl. Add 3 quarts club soda that has been chilled and the frozen limeade concentrate; stir until completely dissolved. Cover and refrigerate.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar and corn syrup.
Add peanut butter and then mix in Rice Krispies.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and cool.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: In ice cream freezer container, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Freeze leftovers.

title: luscious lemon dessert
directions: Mix oleo, flour and pecans together and press into an 8-inch square baking pan; bake 15 minutes at 300°.
Whip cream cheese in mixer until fluffy.
Add powdered sugar and lemon extract.
Blend well.
Fold in whipped cream.
(Cool Whip is fine to use.)
Spread this over baked, cooled crust.
Prepare pudding using 1 1/2 cups milk instead of 2 cups as directed on package.
Spread over cream cheese filling.
Top with more whipped topping.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Pour Eagle Brand milk and coconut cream over top.
Chill.
Top with Cool Whip and cherries.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage in salted, boiling water a few minutes to soften leaves.
Drain on paper towels.
Combine beef, rice, onion, egg, salt and pepper.
Add can of tomato sauce.
Divide mixture into 8 portions and roll in cabbage leaves.
Secure with toothpicks. Place in large skillet.
Pour tomato soup over rolls.
Cover and simmer for 40 minutes, spooning mixture over.

title: chinese slaw
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar.
Add to drained vegetables; toss. Better if made the day before.
Keeps well refrigerated.

title: baked chicken with herb gravy
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in skillet and brown chicken lightly on all sides.
Place chicken in casserole; sprinkle with salt, pepper and rosemary.
Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake 35 minutes or until fork-tender.
Pour juices from casserole into saucepan and cook over high heat until reduced to 1/3 cup.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir in sour cream.
Serve over hot chicken.

title: eggs in sauce
directions: Beat raw egg and add the mayonnaise, mustard and sugar.
Pour over cooked eggs.

title: strawberry cream roll
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil, and water well.
Spread onto two 13 x 18 in. pans, greased well and lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350°F until light brown.
Flip onto clean towel and peel off wax paper. Roll up cake with towel and let cool completely.
Whip cream, adding sugar and vanilla.
Unroll cakes and spread half of cream on cakes, drizzle with syrup.
Roll up, place on plate and spread rest of cream on top.
Drizzle with syrup.

title: zesty chicken
directions: Place chicken in oblong pan (ungreased).
Mix all ingredients except lemon slices.
Pour over chicken.
Cook, uncovered, in a 375° oven.
Occasionally spoon the oil mixture over chicken.
Cook 30 minutes.
Turn; continue in the same manner another 30 minutes, or until thickest part of chicken is cooked.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown meat, celery and spices.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch sprayed pan. Top with vegetables and/or pepperoni slices.
Pour pizza sauce on top. Top with cheese.
Unfold crescent rolls and place them flat on top. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: snowman punch
directions: Bring sugar, water, cloves and cinnamon sticks to boil until sugar dissolves.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Let cool and remove spices.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir with ice cubes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: deluxe potato casserole
directions: Cook and mash potatoes in a mixer (keep hot).
Add cream cheese, egg, dried onion, salt and pepper.
Put in a casserole dish and bake in a 350° oven. This may be made a day ahead and refrigerated.
Potatoes will stay fluffy.

title: strawberry-banana slush punch
directions: Mix together and freeze in containers.
(This recipe serves 50.)
When serving this many, add 4 quarts of strawberry soda. The slush should be removed from the freezer 3 hours before adding the soda in order for it to slush and flavor the drink.
When serving a smaller number of people, use less of the slush and less of the soda.

title: low-fat apple bran muffins
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine Bran Flakes and milk.
Let stand until cereal softens.
Add egg whites and oil; mix well. Add flour mixture and cut up apple.
Pour into lightly greased muffin tins.
Bake in a 400° oven for 18 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: moist tender smoked picnic ham
directions: Place the smoked picnic ham into a heavy Dutch oven filled 2/3 full of water.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bring to a full boil and reduce heat.
Cook for approximately 4 hours.
Save all the juices for a pot of navy beans!!

title: shrimp newburg
directions: Cook noodles, drain, put in baking dish.
Heat soup, milk, cheese and shrimp.
Stir in salad dressing and sherry in double boiler.
Pour over noodles.
Bake 20 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Soften, but don't melt, margarine.
Add sugar; mix with tablespoon.
Ad beaten eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add flour, soda, baking powder and
salt.
Mix
in
the
peanut butter by heaping spoonfuls on greased
pan,
an
inch
apart
on cookie sheet.
Press down and bake at 350°.
Bake about 20 minutes or until slightly browned.
Remove from oven, let rest 5 minutes; then loosen with spatula.
Makes about 2 dozen medium cookies.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients
together, beating well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Separate eggs; beat egg whites to a stiff stand.
Add 6 tablespoons of sugar from the 2 2/3 cups that was measured.
Beat fast.
Remove from mixer.
Put in refrigerator until you get the cake mixed up.
Cream the remaining sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks.
Add part of the flour, beating all the time.
Add 4 tablespoons of cream.
Add the remaining flour, beating all the time.
Add vanilla and then the other 4 tablespoons of cream. Beat good; fold in egg whites.
Pour in well greased and floured tube pan.
Cook 2 hours at 300°.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix condensed milk, eggs, egg white and salt. Add juice gradually. Beat until thick. Add rind. Pour into baked pie shell. Cover with meringue and brown in 350° oven.

title: drunken pork chops
directions: Beat vinegar, water, salt, pepper, garlic powder and paprika. Soak chops in liquid for 1 hour, keep turning.
Drain off vinegar mixture.
Place in a frying pan of hot oil and brown on both sides.
Drain off all of the oil except 1 tablespoon.
Add soup to hot skillet and mix well.
Add a little water and chops.
Cover and simmer on low for 1 hour.

title: texas pralines
directions: Line a cookie sheet with foil, then cover foil with graham crackers.
Boil together for 2 minutes the oleo, sugar and nuts. Pour mixture over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Allow pralines to cool and break into pieces for serving.

title: camp burritos
directions: Spread beans on tortillas.
Sprinkle with onion and cheese. Add meat and salsa.
Add cheese slice.
Roll up tortillas.

title: berried delight
directions: Mix together crumbs, margarine and sugar.
Pat firmly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes; cool.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and milk until smooth.
Fold in half of topping. Spread over cooled crust.
Arrange fruit in layer.
Make pudding and pour over fruit.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight. To serve, spread remaining topping on top and garnish with fruit.

title: dill vegetable dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together and chill.

title: honeyed pot roast
directions: Brown meat and onions over medium heat in cooking oil.
Turn to brown on all sides.
Add remaining ingredients.
Reduce flame. Cover and simmer approximately 3 to 3 1/2 hours or until tender. Serves 8.

title: old time chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook beef roast until "falling apart."
When roast is half done, add 1 bottle of hot or medium picante sauce and let cook into the meat.
Remove from stove and shred into tiny pieces.
Place approximately 1/2 beef mixture or more if tortillas are extra large; add more picante sauce to taste.
Sprinkle heavily with shredded Mexican style cheese (usually a mixture of Monterey Jack, Colby, Cheddar or other hard yellow cheese).
Begin with one side and fold tortilla into an envelope; deep-fry until tortilla is brown.
This will melt the cheese inside.
Serve with salad, chopped lettuce and tomato and other Mexican compliments.

title: no fat creamy dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Let cool.
Divide in half. To each half, add 1/2 fruit with juice and 1/2 of yogurt.
Blend. Put in dessert dishes.
Cool 2 to 3 hours.
Great with fresh fruit also.

title: cornish hens with citrus-sage sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread the chopped onions on the bottom of a baking dish.
Place hens in a single layer on top of onions, cut side down.
Sprinkle with pepper and salt.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Beat up egg in a large bowl.
Mix in sugars.
Stir in flour, sifted with baking powder.
Add salt, vanilla and lemon juice. Mix in apple pieces.
Mix in chopped pecans or walnuts.

title: pepperoni bites
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl by hand.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats and cool 20 minutes.
Cream butter and sugars; add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Then add oatmeal mixture.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients and vanilla.
If desired, blend in 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Saute onions in butter or bacon drippings until brown; stir in all remaining ingredients, except spareribs.
Simmer until mixed and heated.
Pour sauce over ribs and add water to pan to cover meat.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 4 hours until meat falls from bones. Lower oven temperature to 300° to 325° if ribs brown too fast. Leftover sauce freezes well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Cook rice. Add soup, cheese and broccoli to 1/2 to 3/4 package of Ritz crackers. Melt 1/2 stick margarine and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: waffles
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Beat egg whites separately to soft peak and fold into mixture.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all together and chill several hours.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and mushrooms in margarine.
Split chicken breasts in center to make 8 pieces.
Fill all 8 pieces with sauteed vegetables.
Roll from short end and secure with toothpicks.
Grease with margarine 8-inch square baking dish. Place breasts in dish.
Cover, bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter rounds
directions: Spread peanut butter between 2 crackers.
Melt chocolate bark in 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish in microwave for 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir until smooth.
Dip crackers into melted chocolate with tongs and place on waxed paper.
Cool.
Can be stored in refrigerator or freezer.
Makes about 48.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water until tender.
Drain and cool. Marinate in French dressing for at least 1 hour.
Drain and arrange on serving plate with lemon wedge garnish.
(Can use 1/2 cauliflower.)

title: steak and ale marinade
