directions: This marinade can be used on steaks, chicken breast or rump roast.

title: garlic tortilla chips
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brush flour tortillas with melted butter. Sprinkle with garlic salt and cut into wedges.
Place on bake sheets.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: bow tie pasta with chicken
directions: Heat olive oil over medium heat in large skillet.
Saute garlic until golden, stir constantly.
Add chicken strips, saute until white and almost completely cooked.
Add broccoli, saute until crisp-tender.
Add spices and tomatoes, wine, broth and margarine.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes until thoroughly heated.
Toss pasta with chicken mixture.
Serve with Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: candied yams
directions: Grease a baking dish with oleo.
Slice potatoes, long ways; place in baking dish.
Bring to boil the sugar, syrup and oleo, then pour over potatoes in bowl.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy rocky road cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows on baked cake and return to oven until marshmallows are just melted.
Mix frosting, pecans and chocolate chips in a small bowl.
Spread mixture on cooled cake and marshmallows.
Enjoy.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean to remove all stems.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, butter, garlic, onion, salt, pepper and fill caps.
Pour 2 Tbsp. oil in bottom of baking pan.
Place mushrooms in pan. Bake about 10 minutes in moderate oven.
Mushrooms should be tender. Tops should be brown.

title: lemon pie
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until thick and add half to the following egg yolk mixture.
Cook egg yolks 3 minutes, then add butter and lemon juice.
Use baked crust and top with egg whites to which sugar has been slowly added.
Pour over lemon filling and bake at 350° until brown.

title: stewed corn and tomatoes
directions: Cook bacon in an 8 or 9-inch skillet over medium heat, about 5 to 7 minutes or until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.

title: cherry walnut cake
directions: Blend together sugar and shortening.
Sift dry ingredients. Add alternately cherry juice and milk with dry ingredients and vanilla.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Fold into batter.
Add cherries and walnuts.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: donna's beer biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together, Put in a greased muffin pan. Bake 400 degrees for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 large muffins.

title: chocolate break-ups
directions: Butter may be substituted for margarine.

title: sugar-free raisin cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until the water is gone.
Then add applesauce, eggs, oil, sweetener and vanilla.
Mix well and blend in dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
(Drained fruit cocktail may be substituted in place of raisins and water.)

title: herb butter
directions: Cream butter with spices.
Yield: 1/3 cup.
Very good over pasta.

title: olive wreath mold
directions: Make jello according to package directions and let start to set.
Drain crushed pineapple.
Fold all ingredients into jello, whipped cream last.
Unmold on a bed of curly endive lettuce to look like a Christmas wreath.
Decorate with extra sliced stuffed olives.

title: woodpecker food
directions: Melt the lard and peanut butter together, then mix with corn meal and flour.
Place in onion bag and hang from the bird feeder.

title: strawberry cheese mousse
directions: Put 1/4 cool water in blender. Sprinkle gelatin over and stir to soften. Add 1/4 cup boiling water.
Blend, then add remaining 1/4 cup water and all ingredients except strawberries. Blend until smooth. Fold in strawberries.

title: stuffed bacon balls(appetizer)
directions: In medium bowl, mix butter and water until melted.
Add eggs and beat with fork.
Add stuffing and pork sausage.
Cover and refrigerate for 20 minutes.
Roll into balls.
Cut bacon slices into 3 pieces.
Wrap bacon around balls (secure with toothpick). Bake at 400° until crispy.

title: hydrox dessert
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve in hot water.
Add vanilla.
Beat egg whites and add sugar until stiff.
Combine gelatin mixture with eggs and sugar mixture.
Fold in whipped cream, beaten until stiff.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese; mix
well
with
sausage.
Then add Jiffy mix and Tabasco sauce;
mix
well.
Roll
into bite size balls and bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Grease 2 (9-inch) layer pans.
Line bottoms with waxed paper. Mix well dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir in mayonnaise. Gradually stir in water and vanilla until smooth and blended. Pour into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool completely.
Remove from pans.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix powdered sugar, margarine, vanilla, almond extract and egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours. Cut into shapes and place on cookie sheet. Bake until edges are brown, 7 to 8 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: wonderful oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy. Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Then add oats, nuts, raisins and vanilla. Mix well.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Bread and fry chicken cutlets.
Pat dry.
Put aluminum foil on cookie sheet.
Spread out sweet and sour sauce.
Place cutlets on top.
Then spread some more sauce on top of cutlets and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Easy clean up!

title: shirley's fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl. Cover and refrigerate several hours for flavors to blend.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake
at 350° for 1 hour or until mixture is set and golden brown.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together well except chocolate.
Chill for 4 hours.
Roll into balls and with a fork, dip one at a time in the melted chocolate.
Place on wax paper to set.

title: old fashion gingerbread
directions: Mix lard, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add syrup.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add dry mixture to lard, sugar and egg mixture.
Add also milk to dry mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: black fruit cake
directions: Put apples and oranges around and on top after done.

title: cornmeal scrapple(good on cold days)
directions: In a saucepan, combine cornmeal, milk, sugar and salt. Gradually stir in water.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat.
Cook, covered, for 10 minutes more, or until very thick, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; stir in sausage.
Pour into loaf pan that has been greased.
Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate.
To serve, slice 1/3-inch thick.
Dip in flour and brown in butter.
Top with syrup.

title: cheesy hors d'oeuvres
directions: Spread mixture on the English muffins.
Cut into fourths or eighths and bake at 350° until bubbly.
May be frozen before baking.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chopped bell pepper, onion, pineapple and drain.
Soften cream cheese and mix other ingredients.
Form into ball, roll in pecans.

title: cheesy herb loaf
directions: Microwave bacon until crisp, crumble when cooled. Heat unwrapped cream cheese until softened.
Add cheeses and dry mustard.
Add milk, beat until fluffy, add the rest of the ingredients plus crumbled bacon.
Cut French bread in 1 in slices and spread with cheese mixture.
Place loaf on waxed paper and microwave 1 1/2 to 2 minutes until heated through.
Can also be wrapped in foil and heated for 20 to 25 minutes in 350 degree oven.

title: paul hartel party casserole
directions: Saute beef.
When brown and drained, add 2 cans of the tomato sauce.
Put 1 cup of tomato sauce on the bottom of a casserole, 1/2 of the noodles and all of the cheese mixture, then the other half of noodles, then pour the beef and tomato sauce on top.
Bake one hour.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix jello by package directions, leave off 1 cup of the water. Drizzle lemon juice over sliced bananas; coat with the juice. Mix bananas, pineapple
and
marshmallows
in
jello. Chill in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.

title: easy cheesy pasta
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
While noodles are cooking, heat olive oil and garlic in skillet.
Stir in tomatoes and basil; simmer.
Drain noodles, then toss with cheese.
Pour tomato sauce over noodles and serve.
This dish makes a lot of food fast and reheats well.

title: gelatin dessert
directions: Mix together
jello
and sugar.
Mix together water and Knox gelatine, then
add to jello mixture.
Add 4 cups boiling water. Let sit 5 minutes.	Pour the whipping cream; mix well, then pour into
mold	or
cake
pan.	Grease pan with a little mayonnaise before pouring jello in.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: liqueur
directions: Put all ingredients in a large jar.
Let sit for 4 weeks, shaking often.
Then strain through cheesecloth and pour into bottles.

title: crumb cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour pan. Recommend one 13 x 9 pan or two 9 1/2-inch cake pans. Mix sugar, flour and butter into crumb like mixture. Save lots of crumbs for topping. Mix eggs, soda and buttermilk together. Add this to 1st mixture. Pour into pans for baking. Before topping with reserved crumbs, add last 3 ingredients.

title: french oven beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients in a 4 qt. casserole or roaster.
Cover and bake 4 hours at 300 degrees.

title: turkey or chicken barbecue
directions: Melt Crisco in crock-pot.
Saute celery and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until tender.

title: southern meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into balls.
Brown in skillet or oven.
Put browned meat balls in crock-pot.

title: cold rice dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add Marzetti, salt and pepper. Add creamy Italian or Italian dressing, if desired.

title: cream cheese pies
directions: Beat well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 pies.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in casserole.

title: country style cabbage
directions: Shred the cabbage.
Melt the butter in a large skillet and add the cabbage.
Cook over medium heat.
Cook until soft, stirring occasionally.
Add the light cream and simmer.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Saute beef in large skillet.
Add green pepper, celery, onion and salt and cook 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, soup, mushrooms and black olives.
Cook 10 minutes.
Cook noodles.
Place in large roasting pan; pour sauce over noodles and stir to gently mix. Sprinkle with cheese and bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 10 generously.

title: pumpkin seeds
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut open pumpkin and remove insides. Clean pulp from seeds and rinse in water thoroughly.
Place seeds on a cookie sheet in a single layer.
Sprinkle salt on top and bake for 30 minutes.
Let seeds cool before eating.
Salt substitute can be used in place of regular salt.

title: layered taco dip
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan or large platter, spread refried beans into a thin layer.
In small bowl, mix sour cream and taco seasoning mix.
Next, layer sour cream mixture evenly.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
This can be covered and refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel and core apples.
Slice into large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and coat apple slices evenly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cover with another pie crust and close edges as usual.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: easy oven chicken
directions: Cut up chicken.
Coat chicken in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Place on a cookie sheet with the butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: christmas cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, beating well after each addition.
Add jam, walnuts, cherries, raisins, potatoes, coconut and allspice.
Stir in buttermilk.
Add brandy.
Add sifted flour with soda and salt and fold into the batter until smooth.
Bake in two or three layers or in a tube pan in a 250° oven (slow) for about 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Use any preferred icing with nuts.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Combine powdered sugar and peanut butter with fork until blended.
Place evenly in bottom of pie crust.
Place milk and sour cream in bowl.
Add pudding mix, beat until thickened.
Pour half of filling over peanut butter mixture.
Coarsely chop 4 candy cups; sprinkle over filling.
Top with remaining filling.
Spread Cool Whip over filling.
Cut remaining candy cup into 8 pieces; place on top of pie.
Refrigerate.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugar in mixing bowl until well blended.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine dry ingredients in bowl.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool on wire racks.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix and chill.
Add bananas just before serving.

title: mrs. truly conerly's date nut balls
directions: Melt oleo in heavy pan and add sugar.
Stir.
Blend in egg yolks gradually.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook about 1 minute.
Remove from fire.

title: guilty-free pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine at medium speed.
Gradually add egg substitute and beat well.
Combine sour cream and baking soda; stir and set aside.
Combine flour and salt; set aside.
To creamed sugar, margarine and egg mixture, alternately add flour mixture and sour cream mixture; begin and end with flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
(If desired, add apples, peaches, etc.)
Spoon into tube pan coated with Pam and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 35 minutes. Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: bill's refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine vegetables in a jar about 1 1/2-quart size.
Sprinkle with salt and celery seed.
Stir gently and let stand for about 1 hour.
Combine sugar and vinegar.
Stir until sugar dissolves. Pour over vegetables and stir to blend.
Cover and refrigerate. Pickles will be ready to eat in one day.
Keep covered in refrigerator.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Cook raisins in as little water as possible until soft.
Add other ingredients.
Mix and cook until thickened.
Then add vanilla and butter.
Let cool.
Pour into pie shell.
Add meringue or whipped topping to top of pie.

title: pear cheese pie
directions: Use a 9-inch pan.
Slice pears into crust.
Combine yolks
and cream cheese; beat until smooth.
Blend in sour cream and lemon juice.
Combine dry ingredients; add to sour cream mixture.
Mix well; pour over pears.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: mother mulligan's really good goop
directions: Mix cauliflower, sour cream, Mozzarella cheese and salt and pepper and place in casserole dish.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine. Add Italian bread crumbs to margarine until flaky.
Add 3 tablespoons sliced almonds.
Cook on stove for 1 1/2 minutes on medium heat.
Layer on top of casserole and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: tender texas style steaks
directions: Lay steaks in bottom of slow cooker. Combine sugar and ketchup. Pour over steaks. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and a few dashes of Worcestershire sauce. Cover. Cook on high 3 hours and low 3 hours.

title: gob icing
directions: Mix together flour and water.
Stir in milk.
Cook until paste and let cool in refrigerator.
Mix together remaining ingredients, then add paste and mix until smooth.
Frosts 2 (9-inch) or sheet cake.

title: hot chicken salad(serves 6)
directions: Place cubed bread in bottom of greased casserole dish or baking pan.
Mix chicken, onion, green pepper, celery, pimento, mayonnaise, lemon juice, pineapple and water chestnuts together. Layer over bread cubes.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and soup. Pour over chicken layer.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
After baking, immediately sprinkle top with shredded Cheddar cheese and crushed potato chips.

title: date cake
directions: Cut up dates and sprinkle with soda.
Cover with boiling water.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, well beaten.
Add flour and salt and stir to smooth mixture.
Stir in dates, water and nuts.
Pour into slightly greased tube pan.
Bake in a slow 300° oven for 1 hour until golden brown and leaves side of pan.

title: peanut butter chocolate cookies
directions: Beat sugars, margarine, peanut butter, vanilla and egg in bowl until creamy.
Mix in flour, oats, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop dough 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until brown in 350° oven.
For bars, grease 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread dough.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen plus 11 cookies.

title: orange marinated shish kabobs
directions: Microwave chicken until done.
Dice up the meat into 1-inch cubes.
Place meat in glass or plastic bowl.
Combine all the remaining marinade ingredients and pour over the meat cubes. Cover.
Marinate the cubes overnight or longer.
Put meat cubes on skewers and barbecue.

title: easy raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins in water.
Cool and pour into unbaked pie crust. Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix with a spoon.
Spread over top of pie.
Cook at 350° until golden brown, about 40 minutes.

title: sherried fruit
directions: Put all ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Drain fruit, peaches, pears, cherries, pineapple, apricots, plums, apple rings (whatever combination you prefer).
Pour mixture over fruit and refrigerate overnight.
Heat until bubbly and serve warm.

title: gourmet potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, egg whites, onion, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, pickle relish, mayonnaise, vinegar, mustard and celery seed.
Pour over potato mixture; toss lightly.
Refrigerate. Before serving, garnish with grated yolks.
Serves 6.

title: coffee can bread
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; let rise until bubbly.
Add milk to yeast mixture along with 1/3 cup oil.
Add 4 cups flour and salt.
Mix with mixer, then add last 2 cups flour.
Mix by hand and turn out on floured board.
Knead lightly.
Divide into 3 equal parts and put into 3 well-greased coffee cans with lids. Let rise until lids pop off, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° on bottom rack.
Remove from cans at once and butter.

title: new england chowder
directions: In a large pan, place fish and enough water to cover.
Cook over medium heat until fish flakes with a fork (10 minutes).
With slotted spoon, remove from water and break into bite size pieces. Set aside.
Measure the water fish was cooked in and add enough additional water to make 4 cups.
In liquid, cook celery, onion and potatoes until tender.
In a bowl, combine flour and water to make paste.
Stir into liquid.
Cook until boiling. Reduce heat to medium-low.
Add all other ingredients.
Heat through.
Garnish with dried parsley.

title: chicken casserole(serves 12)
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Put in bottom of baking pan.
Cover with cream of celery soup and cream of chicken soup (undiluted). Cover with 1 package of Stove Top stuffing made as package directs. Add 1 cup chicken broth over all.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serve with Wheat Thins or any hard crackers.

title: spinach ziti
directions: Roll dough.
Put it up in the air.
Put cheese on it and all that kind of stuff you put on it and nothing else.
Put it in the oven on 6 degrees for two minutes, then give it to your schoolmates.

title: layered bean dip
directions: In a medium bowl, mix refried beans, green chilies and taco seasoning mix.
Spread on a 12-inch round serving platter.
Blend avocado, lemon juice and 1/2 cup taco sauce until smooth.
Spread on top of avocado mixture. Top with shredded lettuce, cheese and taco sauce.
Serve with nachos or tortilla chips.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: In a skillet combine butter or margarine, green pepper and onion.
Cook until tender.
Next add tomatoes, salt, pepper and eggplant.
Cook slow for 10 minutes or until eggplant is tender. Pour the mixture into a casserole dish and sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
During the last 10 minutes of baking put shredded cheese on top.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and egg.
Add pumpkin.
Sift together flour, baking powder and spices and add gradually to rest of ingredients.
Fold in raisins or chopped nuts.
Drop by teaspoons on baking sheet and bake in oven at 375° for about 15 minutes.
When cool, frost with thin icing.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients into 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes, until chicken salad bubbles and boils.
Top with potato chips and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: egg brunch
directions: Cube and butter slices of bread.
Grate Cheddar cheese.
Brown sausage and drain.
Beat together eggs, dry mustard, salt and half and half.
Layer bread, sausage and cheese.
Repeat.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Bake at 300° until firm.

title: zeppoli
directions: Dissolve the yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Put the remaining water in a large pan and add the flour all at once, beating vigorously.
Beat in the yeast and quickly turn the dough out onto a pastry board.
Knead with greased hands until smooth.

title: lettuce cauliflower salad
directions: Layer in order written.
Let set overnight.
Stir well before serving.

title: pineapple mandarin salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons juice.
Combine reserved juice, mayonnaise, yogurt and onions; set aside.
Arrange pineapple, oranges and chicken on lettuce-lined plates.
Serve with dressing.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oven omelet
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 9-inch baking pan with cooking spray.
Melt margarine in skillet; add mushrooms.
Stir-fry until tender; drain and set aside.
Combine egg, milk, flour and pepper. Beat with whisk until bubbly.
Stir in 1 cup of cheese, mushrooms and bacon or ham.
Pour into prepared baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until center is set.
Serves 6.

title: chicken broccoli rice bake
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in oleo.
Layer in the bottom of a 2-quart buttered baking dish rice, onion and mushrooms.
Add 2/3 to 1 can undiluted soup and chicken.
Cover with 5 to 6 slices of Velveeta cheese.
Cover with cooked broccoli (cook until crisp-tender stage, do not overcook; salt and pepper broccoli slightly).
Top with 3 or 4 more slices of Velveeta.
Mix soup with one can of milk.
Pour over entire casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: You may add more raisins, if desired.

title: sunshine muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flours, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add remaining ingredients; stir just until moistened (batter may be lumpy). Fill greased or paper-lined muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until top of muffin springs back when lightly touched.
Yield: 15 to 18 muffins.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Dredge chicken in flour.
In large, heavy skillet, brown chicken in hot oil until golden.
Add onion, garlic, potatoes, salt, thyme, bay leaf, pepper and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 25 minutes, or until chicken and potatoes are almost tender.
Add beans; cover and cook 5 minutes, or until chicken and vegetables are tender.
Discard bay leaf. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: blender bearnaise
directions: Place all the ingredients, except the butter, in the blender. Blend for approximately 5 seconds.
Let the butter cool to room temperature, then gradually add slowly to blender.
The sauce should thicken.
If the butter is too hot, it will not thicken.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: oatmeal mushroom patties
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Add mushrooms and rest of ingredients.
Mix and form patties.
Fry in oil until brown.
Place in casserole.
Cover with gravy.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: caesar pasta cold
directions: Boil ziti according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Add the quantity you prefer for the next 5 ingredients.
Mix until all blended.
Let stand for 20 minutes. Makes 5 to 6 servings.
Great taste!

title: broccoli stove top casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Cook Stove Top stuffing (moist).
Combine eggs, soup, onion and add 1/2 cup mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Place layer of broccoli in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then add a layer of soup mixture and cheese.
Top with stuffing.
Pour melted oleo on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Drain water from cucumber, making sure no moisture is left. Mix all ingredients in blender.
Serve cold with corn chips or potato chips.
Makes 3 cups.
Serves 12.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Grease a large baking dish.
Layer pork chops, sliced potatoes and mushroom soup.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: country company potatoes
directions: Heat soup and 1/2 cup butter; add cheese, sour cream and minced onions.
Combine with potatoes and pour into 13 x 9 casserole dish. Refrigerate overnight.

title: sour cream rhubarb pie
directions: Put rhubarb in pie shell.
Mix sour cream, sugar, flour and egg yolks.
Pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool slightly.
Add 6 tablespoons sugar gradually to the beaten egg white. Spread over pie.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes more.

title: old fashioned fudge brownies(50 years)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating only well enough to mix.
Add melted chocolate, stirring by hand.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix eggs, flour and cheese.
Cook broccoli; strain and dry. Add to egg mixture.
Use 7 x 11-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Bake all ingredients in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pop's caesar salad
directions: First Layer:
1 head lettuce, chopped and placed in a large 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: oven french toast
directions: Dip bread
in
mixture of eggs, sugar, salt, nutmeg and milk and
place	in
greased
oblong
pan.
Pour remaining egg mixture over
all.	Bake for 5 minutes at 475°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve with jelly or syrup and sausage.

title: decadent triple layer mud pie
directions: Mix chocolate and condensed milk until well blended. Pour into crust; sprinkle with pecans. Pour milk into large bowl; add pudding mixes. Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes or until well blended. (Mixture will be thick.) Spoon 1 1/2 cups of the pudding over pecans in crust. Add 1/2 of the whipped topping to remaining pudding; stir with wire whisk until blended. Spread over pudding in crust. Top with remaining whipped topping. Refrigerate 3 hours. Makes 10 servings.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix together.
Sprinkle sugar on top and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Put jelly in center if you wish.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Pour marinade over vegetables and leave overnight.
Pour off excess liquid before serving.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Mix all together and bake in uncovered baking dish for 2 1/2 hours at 325°.
Makes approximately 8 servings.

title: potato salad
directions: Cool and peel the potatoes.
Layer potatoes, sprinkle with chopped green onion tops, salt and pepper to taste.
Make a sauce of the mayonnaise, oil, vinegar and sugar.
Dot sauce around and repeat layers.

title: mama's basic honey chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Rub 1 tablespoon butter over chicken. Poke a fork into each side of the breasts.
Pour half of the honey over both chicken breasts.
Bake in a deep pan for about 45 minutes.
Pour the remaining 1/2 of honey over the chicken and bake about 10 to 15 more minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy. Blend in vanilla and cooled chocolate. Add egg, well beaten. Stir together flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with water, beating after each addition. Spread batter in greased and lightly floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with chocolate pieces. Arrange walnut halves over top.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until cake springs back when touched in center. Cool in pan.

title: seafood creole
directions: Prepare roux by melting margarine in a large skillet.
Over medium heat, blend flour and stir constantly until roux is dark brown.
Be careful not to scorch.
In a one-cup measure, add reserved tomato liquid and enough water to equal 1 cup.
Stir into roux and blend until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook and simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove bay leaves and serve Creole over hot rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: my ma's dinner rolls
directions: Mix warm water with yeast.
Add scalded milk, salt, sugar and shortening.
Add enough flour for the right consistency you need for rolls.
Bake rolls at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and pat dry.
Prick each potato with a fork in 1 or 2 places.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Cut a thin slice off flat side of each potato.
Scoop out the pulp into a bowl, leaving shells intact.
Beat pulp with the egg yolks until fluffy.
Beat in butter and cream.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: raspberry pretzel jello
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Melt butter with sugar; add to the crushed pretzels.
Bake at 350°
for 10 minutes.

title: fruit slushy
directions: Combine 1 can of each frozen ingredient in blender.
Add enough ice to fill container.
Process until mixture is slushy. Empty blender container.
Repeat with remaining ingredients. Serve immediately.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: franco-american spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Saute separately onions, pepper and mushrooms in butter.
Add tomatoes, etc., to hamburger.
Add spaghetti and beans.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix well.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: oyster stew
directions: Cook oysters over low heat in oyster liquor for 3 minutes, or until edges begin to curl.
Stir in remaining ingredients except paprika.
Heat to a near boil.
Garnish with paprika and serve immediately.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Beat together thoroughly the shortening, sugar, eggs, baking soda and vanilla.
Add flour, nuts and potato chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; add nuts and raisins.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs; add applesauce and melted shortening.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir just until blended.
Pour into a greased loaf pan (8 x 4 x 4-inch).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool. Freezes well.

title: banana bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine hot water, bran and raisins and set aside.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon and set aside.

title: pudding chip cookies
directions: Mix flour and soda.
Combine sugars, pudding mix and vanilla in large mixer bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chips and nuts. Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheets about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix all ingredients (except vegetable oil) thoroughly in a bowl; shape into croquettes, heaping tablespoon-size is best. Heat oil in skillet and fry croquettes, turning frequently.
Makes 15 to 18 croquettes.

title: french iced coffee
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot coffee; cool.
Add other ingredients. Pour into milk cartons to freeze.
Remove from freezer 2 hours before serving.
Mix and serve very icy.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat mixture for 4 minutes.
Bake in 3 pans for 20 minutes. Cool.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix oleo and flour; spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat in pan and bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: cheerio cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, water, vanilla and egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls, about 2 inches apart, on greased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: pizza dough
directions: Measure water into a bowl and sprinkle in yeast, stirring until dissolved.
Stir in additional flour and other ingredients. Turn out on lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic, working in more flour if dough is sticky.
Allow dough to rest 5 minutes before patting out in pans.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
It makes two 13 1/4 x 9-inch pans.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Increase amounts and spread over chicken, beef and pork chops. I add chopped onion for better flavor.
Can be used for barbecue on a bun.

title: milky way cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Melt 6 Milky Way bars with 1/2 cup butter; set aside and cool.
Cream sugar and other 1/2 cup butter.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, then add vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Alternately, add buttermilk and flour.
Mix in cooled candy and nuts.
Pour into 12 cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour and 20 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove.
Melt 1 Milky Way with 1 tablespoon butter.
Drizzle over cooled cake.

title: salmon stuffed shells
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, mixing well.
Stuff shells. Cover with spaghetti sauce Bake in shallow pan that has been sprayed with PAM at 350° for 15 - 20 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 6.
306 calories per serving.

title: smothered steak
directions: Put steak strips, flour, salt and pepper in crock-pot.
Stir well to coat steak.
Add all other ingredients.
Cover and cook on low 8 hours or on high 4 hours.
Serve with rice.

title: layered delight
directions: To prepare as crust, mix flour, sugar, butter or oleo and nuts. Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool crust.
Mix well cream cheese and powdered sugar and spread on crust.
Then spread on 1 cup Cool Whip and vanilla pudding (mixed with 2 cups milk).
Pour over crust, then add 1 cup Cool Whip on top.

title: low-fat fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8 x 8-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In a medium bowl, sift together cocoa powder, flour, baking powder and salt.
In a separate large bowl, cream together margarine and sugar.
Whisk in egg whites, natural applesauce and vanilla.
Stir flour mixture into egg mixture until combined.
Pour mixture into prepared pan and bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until firm.
Cool before cutting into squares.
Makes 12 servings.

title: heath bits pecan pie
directions: Cover the bottom of a 9-inch pie shell with Heath bits.
In a mixing bowl, combine eggs, sugar, corn syrup, butter and vanilla; mix well.
Add pecans.
Pour mixture over the Heath bits in the pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes, or until pie is done.
Test with a knife.
When the filling does not stick to knife, the pie is done.

title: school barbecue sauce
directions: Place butter into large saucepan and slowly brown lightly. Add onions and garlic; saute.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until smooth and well blended.
Place over heat and allow to simmer until thickened.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: barbecued butterflied leg of lamb
directions: Insert 3 to 4 skewers lengthwise in leg of lamb to prevent meat from curling when cooking.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over the lamb.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 4 hours or more.

title: thumper's tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Open the tuna can.
Empty the contents into a strainer held over the sink and let the water drain off.
Put the tuna in a small dish.
With a fork, break it up into little pieces.
Open the can of peas.
Empty the contents into the strainer over the sink.
Set the drained peas aside. Open the can of soup.
Empty the contents into a 1 1/2-quart casserole and stir.
Stir in the milk a little at a time.
Add the tuna, peas and noodles to the casserole and stir everything together.

title: easy dream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in an ungreased pan.
After cooling, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and cook in salted water until almost tender. Drain. Mix vegetables, soup and 1/2 of stuffing. Pour into a buttered casserole and place remaining stuffing on top. Bake in moderate oven about 30 minutes. Be sure top is brown.

title: indian style spaghetti
directions: Saute in hot oil, onions, tomatoes and spices.
Add cooked spaghetti.
Stir until well mixed.
Serve hot.

title: cornmeal rolls
directions: Cook cornmeal, sugar, salt, shortening and milk until thick (like cooked cereal).
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast that has been dissolved, then eggs.
Beat thoroughly.
Add flour to form soft dough.
Knead well.
Place in bowl.
Cover; let rise.
Punch down. Roll out to 1-inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Brush with melted butter.
Dust with cornmeal.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Cover.
Let rise.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Yields 18 rolls.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: english tea scones
directions: Place egg in a 1-cup liquid measuring cup.
Add enough buttermilk to equal 1 cup; set aside.
In a mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in raisins and baking pieces.
Add buttermilk mixture.
Stir, just until dough clings together.

title: "best" play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add boiling water and oil. Stir.
Knead and add food coloring as desired.
Store in airtight container.
Keeps for months.

title: fruit rhapsody
directions: The smooth, creamy dressing for these fresh summer fruits is made with velvety Kraft mayonnaise and Philadelphia brand cream cheese.
For the salad, arrange fruit on lettuce-covered platter or tiered server.
Serve with.

title: preacher's casserole
directions: Mix soups and sour cream.
Add corn, beans, onion and cheese. Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Crush crackers and put on top.
Pour melted butter over top. Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: easy stew
directions: Mix all together.
Cover and bake 5 hours in a 275° oven.
Do not uncover until done.

title: cauliflower bake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large saucepan; bring to a boil. Cover and reduce heat; cook 5 minutes or until tender. Drain and set aside.

title: old-fashioned fried chitterlings
directions: Cut boiled chitterlings in 5-inch pieces and place in batter. Fry in hot fat until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Mix top 5 ingredients in shallow dish.
Coat pork chops. Brown in oil.
Add last 3 ingredients.
Bake at 350° one hour, adding additional pineapple juice if necessary for consistency. Serve with rice.

title: flank steak sauce
directions: Mix together.
Put flank steak slices in bowl with sauce and marinate overnight.
Best grilled outdoors.

title: minted hot cocoa mix
directions: Place candy in heavy-duty plastic bag.
Crush with mallet. Combine candy and remaining ingredients. Store in airtight container.

title: strawberry parfait pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large mixing bowl and beat with electric mixer at highest speed until soft mounds form when beaters are raised (between 5 and 8 minutes).
Beat the whipping cream until thick.
Fold into the strawberry mixture by hand or at lowest speed of mixer.
Spoon into baked shell or graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle with crumbs and freeze until firm (4 to 6 hours). Cover.

title: corn for freezer
directions: Cook 10 minutes and put in heat and serve bags.
Very good!

title: salmon loaf
directions: Melt butter or margarine and add flour.
Stir until smooth and well blended.
Gradually add milk.
Cook until thickened and smooth.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and place in a well-greased loaf pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Yields 4 servings.

title: never-fail corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add egg, milk and melted oleo.
(I add a little more milk and always cool the butter.)
Mix and pour into greased muffin pans.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: paper bag apple pie
directions: Peel, core and quarter each apple.
Then halve each quarter. Place in large bowl.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and nutmeg in a cup.
Sprinkle over apples; toss to coat well. Spoon into pastry shell and drizzle with lemon juice.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup flour in bowl; cut in butter.
Sprinkle over apples.
Slide pie into brown bag.
Fold open end twice and fasten with paper clips.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 1 hour.

title: salmon fritters
directions: Beat egg with salt.
Add potatoes.
Mix salmon from which all bones have been removed.
Then add 1/2 cup of cracker meal.
Roll into small patties and then roll in remaining cracker meal.
Fry in hot fat until a golden brown.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans, together.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 30 minutes.
Place pecan halves on top to garnish.

title: lemon crumb pie
directions: Cover the bread crumbs with the water; leave for 20 minutes. Add the egg yolks (slightly beaten), juice and rind of lemon, butter, salt and sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour filling into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes in 400° oven.
Cool and cover with sweetened whipped cream.

title: taco lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large saucepan or large skillet, brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning, garlic, cayenne pepper and water.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Set aside.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Place 6 tortillas in bottom of pan, overlapping and extending up sides slightly.
Layer 1 cup salsa, 1/2 meat mixture, 1/2 cup green onions, 1 cup sour cream mixture and 2 cups combined cheeses.
Repeat again, starting with tortillas.
Top with 6 tortillas and remaining salsa.
Bake 30 minutes.
Remove.
Add remaining cheese.
Bake 10 more minutes or until cheese melts.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: chinese pea salad solo
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill well.
Drain and serve, reserving vinegar for leftovers.

title: beefy cheese ball
directions: Cut beef into small pieces and mix with all other ingredients very thoroughly.
Roll into a ball and wrap in wax paper.
Chill.

title: saucy meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, tomato sauce, onion, egg, green pepper, salt and pepper. Mix well and form into a loaf and place in loaf pan.

title: low-cal congealed salad
directions: Mix together Cool Whip, jello and cottage cheese.
Fold in oranges and pineapple.
Put in shallow dish.
Chill for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: sugar-free ice cream
directions: Blend all ingredients except vanilla.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture will coat spoon.
Do not boil.
Remove from burner and add vanilla.
Chill.
Follow directions for freezing regular ice cream.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and corn meal.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add milk, butter, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Pour in 8 1/2 or 9-inch unbaked pie shells and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour batter into a greased shallow baking dish.
Bake for approximately 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool.

title: crab and macaroni casserole(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove cartilage and shells from crabmeat.
Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain. Turn into greased 1 1/4-quart casserole.
Top with crabmeat.
Place half the bread pieces and half the cheese in a blender.
Whirl until mixture is finely chopped, about 5 seconds, and set aside.

title: water chestnuts in bacon
directions: Mix brown sugar and soy sauce in a shallow casserole.
Stir in water chestnuts and marinate 1 to 2 hours.
Wrap each chestnut with a strip of bacon.
Set on broiling pan and bake 15 minutes at 425° or until bacon is crisp.
Serve hot.

title: italian casserole
directions: Brown meat in hot fat with onion, add garlic and oregano, cook noodles; drain and add to meat. Combine water and tomato soup and add to above mixture. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake until the cheese melts at 400 degrees.

title: barley soup
directions: In 6-quart saucepan brown meat.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook until onion is tender; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except frozen vegetables.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, simmer 50 to 60 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add frozen vegetables. Cook about 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
More water can be added if needed.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add onion, milk and beaten egg. Drop by spoonful into fat and brown until crisp and browned. Drain on paper towel.

title: microwave meat loaf(low-fat)
directions: Mix ingredients together and make into a mound with flat top. Place in casserole dish leaving space around.
Microwave on High for 7 minutes.
Turn 1/3 way around, then cook for 6 minutes, turn 1/3 around again and cook for 5 minutes more.

title: snickers cookies
directions: Wrap cookie dough around bite-size candy bars and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet before removing.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In a 1 qt. greased casserole dish, mix soup, milk, pepper and macaroni. Spread breadcrumbs mixed with margarine over top. Bake 20 minutes at 400°. Serves 4.

title: bacon tomato cups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Coarsely chop bacon, tomato and onion. Shred Swiss cheese and mix all ingredients except biscuits. Separate each biscuit into 3 thinner biscuits.
Lay each biscuit over a mini-muffin pan cup and mold around muffin cup, leaving center hollow to fill with bacon mixture.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until golden.
Yield:
30 appetizers.

title: mustard sauce or dip
directions: Add vinegar to rest of mixture and cook in a double boiler slowly or until thick.
Good hot or cold.
Wonderful on ham.

title: peppermint angel food cake
directions: Follow directions on box.
Take out about 1/3 to 1/2 of the batter and add peppermint and food coloring.
Mix.
Drop batter in tube pan, alternating red and white.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Cream cheese with sugar, beat in egg and stir in chips.
Make cake according to package and fill cupcake tins 2/3 full.
Drop 1 teaspoon of cheese mixture into each cupcake.
Bake as directed on box.

title: wild rice pilaf
directions: Saute onion, pepper and drained mushrooms in butter just until tender.
Add rice and cook, stirring, 5 minutes.
Stir in broth, bay leaf, salt and seasoning packet from rice package.
Pour mixture into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until rice is tender.
Remove bay leaf and stir.
Yields 6 servings.

title: lemon, pineapple coconut cake
directions: Bake this cake in an oblong cake pan as directed on package. Cook the lemon pie filling as directed on the box, only add 1/2 cup more sugar and the can of crushed pineapple, including the juice, stirring constantly until thick.
Remove from heat and add the coconut.
Cover the entire cake with this topping; refrigerate until cold.
This topping also makes a good dessert and makes enough to keep a bowl for yourself.
Enjoy!!

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco. Add eggs, one at a time. Add soda to hot water and then add to milk. Gradually add to the Crisco and sugar mixture. Add salt and flavoring. Add flour gradually, beating well. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix together ingredients in order as listed.
Pour in loaf pans (makes 2).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
To this mixture, add bread cubes; stir.
Add cheese and sausage.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: wax beans in creole sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion, celery and hamburg for about 5 minutes or until soft.
Add tomatoes, increase heat and cook 5 minutes.
Add beans and bean liquid.
Simmer about 10 minutes longer.
Add seasoning and serve hot.

title: easy blackberry cobbler
directions: Cook berries in about 1/2 cup sugar and 2 cups water.
Boil for 5 to 7 minutes.
Mix flour and 1 cup sugar.
Add to berries.
Pour in pan and pour melted butter over top.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cobbler can also be made with strawberries, blueberries, or peaches.

title: pineapple bread
directions: Mix well and bake in a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Yields 1 loaf.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together eggs, sugars, shortening and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients gradually.
Stir in chocolate chips.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine and toss with stuffing mix; set aside.
Mix all other ingredients in large bowl.
Add half of stuffing mix; pour into greased casserole dish and top with remaining stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
This freezes nicely.

title: italian meat pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, combine meat, crumbs, egg, bouillon and seasoning; mix well.
Press on bottom and up sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 15 minutes; pour off fat.
Spoon pizza sauce over crust.
Top with mushrooms, green pepper, onion and cheese.
Bake 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: yummy biscuits
directions: Let biscuits thaw until they can be sliced easily. Cut each biscuit into 4 triangles; place in a single layer on baking sheet. Sprinkle cheese evenly over biscuits. Melt margarine in microwave and drizzle all over biscuits. Bake in 350° oven until brown and done.

title: garlic bread
directions: Take biscuits from can.
Place them together in a row and cut down the center.
Sprinkle with garlic.
Put butter on and bake until done.

title: stuffed chicken breasts with mushroom sauce
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Stir hot water, butter and contents of vegetable/seasoning packet in bowl until butter is melted.
Add stuffing crumbs and egg; stir until moistened.
Spoon stuffing onto each breast; add 1 slice of cheese.
Wrap chicken around stuffing and cheese.
Place seam side down in shallow greased baking dish.
Place any remaining stuffing in center of dish. Combine soup and water; pour over chicken and stuffing.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until chicken is thoroughly cooked.

title: super hamburgers
directions: Combine all ingredients but the oil.
Mix well.
Shape into patties.
Brush with oil.
Broil 4 to 6 minutes on each side, depending on the degree of doneness desired.

title: christmas tea
directions: Combine tea bags, cinnamon sticks, whole cloves and 2 cups water.
Bring to a boil.
Steep for about 20 minutes.
Mix Jell-O, pineapple juice, 2 cups hot water and sugar with tea bag mixture. Serve chilled or hot.

title: pinto beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in a bowl with water covering beans. Wash and rinse beans the next morning.
Pick out dirt, stones or bad beans.
Place in covered pot with all other ingredients, using enough water to cover beans well.
Cook in crock-pot all day, or bring to boil on regular stove, simmering for 2 to 3 hours.
Watch and keep beans covered in water.

title: brussels sprouts with walnuts
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine Brussels sprouts and water. Cook, covered, on 100% power (High) for 8 to 10 minutes or until fork-tender, stirring after 5 minutes.
Drain.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Let stand, covered, while preparing topping.

title: ground beef soup
directions: Cook beef, onion and garlic until beef is brown.
In large pot, put all ingredients except green beans.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 40 minutes.
Add green beans, continue simmering for 10 minutes.

title: seafood salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain in cold water.
Cut crab sticks into small pieces.
Run cold water over shrimp.
Drain.
Boil eggs. Cut red pepper small.
Cut green pepper small.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Separate crescent rolls into 2 long oblong sections.
Do not separate into individual rolls.
Press out as thin as possible. Spread each section with the uncooked sausage.
Roll up like a jelly roll cake, beginning with the longest side.
Wrap in freezer wrap and freeze until ready to use.
When ready, while still frozen, slice in 1/4-inch slices.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Drain on paper towels and serve.

title: beef brisket barbecue
directions: Rub meat with salt.
Place on a 20 x 15-inch piece of double thickness heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Stir together remaining ingredients; pour on meat.
Fold foil over meat and seal securely. Place on a grill 5 inches from medium coals.
Cook, turning once, 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender (10 to 12 servings).

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Beat eggs.
Add rest of ingredients in order given.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.

title: classic green bean casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in beans and 1/2 cup onion.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Stir; top with remaining onions. Bake 5 minutes more. Serves 5.

title: mondal bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder and almond extract; mix well.
Add nuts and chips by hand.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Make each a log shape.
Bake on a floured cookie sheet for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
When cooled, cut into slices.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large bowl. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Pour into greased 9-inch pan. Drain peaches well. Reserve juice. Place peaches evenly over batter. Combine cream cheese, peach juice (3 tablespoons) and sugar. Mix until fluffy. Spoon over batter to within 1 inch of edge. Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon. Sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Crust will be brown, filling will be soft. Store in refrigerator.

title: one pan cake
directions: Stir together flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar, cocoa, soda and salt in an ungreased 12 x 8-inch baking pan.
Make 3 wells in mixture; pour oil in one, vinegar in one and vanilla in another.
Pour in coffee and stir all with a fork until well mixed.
Spread into an even layer.
Combine 1/3 cup sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle half over batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cinnamon sugar over hot cake.
Cool 15 to 20 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Cook stuffing as directed on box.
Cook chicken then cut into little pieces.
Mix all three ingredients together in a large bowl, put in a 9x13 cake pan.
Bake on 350 for 35 minutes, then serve.

title: lemon cake pudding(serves 6)
directions: Stir together flour, sugar and salt.
Blend together egg yolks, lemon juice, milk and lemon peel.
Combine liquid and dry ingredients; beat until smooth.
Fold in egg whites.

title: homemade chicken pot pie
directions: Combine chicken.
Add vegetables.
Mix broth and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Then combine milk, flour and butter.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan's honey cookies
directions: In mixer bowl, beat sugar and butter until light.
Add eggs, honey and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Stir together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir into beaten mixture, blending well.
Stir in oats and chopped pecans.
Chill until firm.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Heat onion and butter until onion is tender.
In bowl, combine onion, corn, eggs, cracker crumbs and cheese.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or lightly brown and set.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Wash
chicken and place in a 13-inch pan.
Mix together soup, dressing
and
jam.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb pudding
directions: Mix together white sugar, flour, soda, salt and butter.
Add sour cream or milk.
Spread over bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix rhubarb, brown sugar and hot water together.
Pour this over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
When done, the cake is on top.

title: scrumptious
directions: Mix flour and Crisco like pie crust until crumbly.
Add 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Press in pan and bake about 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Sprinkle dry jello over cottage cheese.
Add fruits.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: bloody mary
directions: Mix together and serve over ice.
Serves 8.

title: ginger lime punch
directions: Pour concentrates into punch bowl. Stir in candied ginger. Chill for 2 hours or longer. Add 6 cups cold water. Pour ginger ale down side of bowl. Garnish with citrus fruit slices.
Yield: 20 servings.

title: fruit bars
directions: Mix together the shortening, sugar, egg and orange rind.
Stir in the orange juice, flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add raisins, candied fruit and nuts.
Spread very thinly onto a greased cookie sheet and bake at 350°.
Do not overbake or they will dry out.
Ice with powdered sugar icing made with a little butter and lemon juice.

title: beef pie
directions: Press raw hamburger in 9-inch pie dish to form crust.
Make dressing as instructed.
Spoon into crust.
Top with soup.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit pie filling to can
directions: Bring to a
boil:
water and sugar, then add clear jell and cook to thicken.
Add fruit and put in cans.
Process 20 minutes.

title: tamale soup
directions: Brown beef with onion and pepper in oil in a large skillet or Dutch oven. Drain off fat. Add corn and bouillon that has been dissolved in the hot water. Add the other ingredients except the tamales and cheese. Cook on low heat until the flavors are blended. Thirty minutes before serving, cut the tamales into 1-inch pieces and add to the soup. Top each serving with cheese and serve with tortilla chips. Great soup.

title: golden fish fillets
directions: Lightly beat together the egg, mustard and salt in a shallow dish.
Put the potato flakes in another shallow dish.
Dip the fish fillets in egg mixture, then roll in potato flakes to coat. Heat oil in a large skillet.
Fry fish for 3 or 4 minutes on each side, until it is golden brown and flakes easily with a fork.
I use a Fry Daddy to deep fry.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients in a baking dish (do not drain corn). Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Mix other ingredients and let stand a few hours.
Mix well with broccoli.

title: spaghetti and beef balls
directions: Combine beef, grated cheese, green pepper, egg and pepper with 1 teaspoon of salt.
Shape into balls.
Saute bacon in a heavy pan until fat melts.
Add beef balls and brown slowly on all sides. Add margarine and onion.
Add the other 1 teaspoon salt, tomatoes, tomato paste and sugar.
Simmer, as slowly as possible, for 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Pour over hot, drained spaghetti. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve with crisp salad and bread.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix sugar and salt together and pour over cucumbers and onion and let set for 1 hour.
Then add oil and vinegar.
Mix all together.
Chill and serve.
May add diced tomatoes, if desired.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Mix crushed pretzels (except reserved 3/4 c.), melted margarine and 3 Tbsp. sugar together.
Press mixture in 9 x 13 pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: yummy jello
directions: Add 2 cups boiling water to gelatin, stir until dissolved. Add 2 cups of cold water. Chill.
Just before set, add 2 big spoonfuls of Cool Whip.
Mix and chill until set.

title: broccoli medley
directions: Cook broccoli according to pacakage directions.
Do not drain. Cook celery and onion in butter until clear.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles up well. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken crescent roll
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl, except lettuce and tomato. Place mix in rolled out crescent with points to center of tray, forming a circle. Roll up, making a solid ring. Put on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° to 375° for 20 minutes. Garnish center with shredded lettuce and sliced tomato.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Finish filling jar with water.
Cover and let soak 3 weeks. Drain and cover with sugar, 5 pounds or so.

title: mama's egg custard
directions: Separate egg yolks.
Beat these, adding 1/2 cup of the milk. In measuring cup, add the flour to the sugar.
Mix these and to the mixture, add the other 1/2 cup of milk.
Combine the 2 mixtures and stir.
Add vanilla flavoring if desired.

Pour this into a pie shell, which has been placed on the stove burner, on low heat for about one minute or just long enough to blister but not to brown. Cook the pie in an oven set at 350° until firm.
Beat egg whites with 4 tablespoons sugar; spread this on the custard and brown.

title: chocolate dream
directions: Mix and spread in bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: rice breakfast casserole
directions: Mix together.
Pour into greased pan; top with 1 can fried onions.
Bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: chicken fried
directions: Soak chicken overnight in milk, turning several times; drain. Place dry ingredients in a plastic bag and shake pieces to coat. Fry chicken in hot oil until golden brown; drain.

title: broccoli casserole (3)
directions: Layer in a 9 X 13 pan: the rice, then broccoli.
Melt butter/oleo, saute onion in it, add salt, pepper & flour. Add milk and bring to a boil to thicken. Add ham, pour on top of broccoli. Layer with cheese, cover with small croutons.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Also, ingredients may be put together and frozen.	When needed, take out and thaw, then bake.

title: baked beans(cholesterol free)
directions: Wash the beans; soak overnight.
Parboil for 15 minutes in the morning.
Add the onion, salt, pepper, mustard and ketchup to bottom of bean pot.
Add parboiled beans.
Add over the beans the molasses and oil, mixed together.
Add boiling water to which has been added the baking soda.
Cover beans with hot water.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours, or until tender.

title: cranberry cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and spices together.
Add rolled oats and raisins.
Combine cranberry sauce, shortening, egg and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients until moistened.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: maraschino cherry nut cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) layer pans or 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan. Cream together shortening and sugar.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Add alternately with the cherry juice and milk to shortening and sugar.
Stir in nuts and cherries. Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: festive glazed ham
directions: In a roasting pan, heat ham according to directions.
Blend 1 jar cherry preserves with 1/4 cup brandy.
When ham is almost heated through, pour preserves and brandy over top of ham.	Baste several times.
Serve ham hot or chilled with smooth Curried Mustard Cream.

title: cousin fannie's stuffed cabbage
directions: Mix together meat, rice, sugar, lemon and salt.
Remove core from cabbage.
Place head in boiling water until leaves soften. Peel off leaves.
Place some mixture on each leaf and wrap.
Shred leftover cabbage.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: To soften tortillas, dip in hot oil in skillet and drain on paper towel.
Or you can spray them with nonstick cooking oil, stack in foil, cover tightly and heat in the oven.
This allows them to become limp and easy to fill.
Mix the soup, 2 cups broth, about 3/4 cup of cheese and green chilies in saucepan.
Heat until cheese melts.

title: tomato and herb bruschetta
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in a bowl.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
(Prepare 2 hours before serving to blend flavors.) Let stand at room temperature.
Spoon onto bread and serve.

title: microwave mexican meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine turkey, 1/2 cup soup, the onion, peppers, corn chips, garlic, chili powder, cumin, oregano, salt and egg; mix well.
In microwave safe, 5 to 6-cup ring mold, place half of the meat mixture; sprinkle with half the cheeses.
Top with remaining meat mixture.
Cover with waxed paper; place paper towels underneath dish to soak up any dripping.
Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes, rotating dish once after 4 minutes.
Drain off excess liquid; invert loaf onto serving platter.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese.
In medium glass bowl, combine remaining soup, the milk, sour cream, chili powder and pepper.
Microwave on high 2 minutes or until heated through.
Serve with turkey ring.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: mamie's meatloaf
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and pour into 8x4 loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Drain. Spread on topping of ketchup and brown sugar.
Bake about 15 minutes longer. Let cool about 30 minutes then slice and serve.

title: honey mustard marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Use to brush on chicken while grilling.
Marinate chicken in refrigerator for 2 to 8 hours before grilling.
Marinate pork tenderloin in refrigerator for 8 hours before grilling.
Yields 1 1/3 cups.

title: apple cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Peel and slice or dice apples. Beat oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Separately mix together salt, baking soda, cinnamon and flour.
Add dry ingredients to oil mixture.
Add apples and nuts.
Mixture will be heavy.
Use wooden spoon and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: special pea salad
directions: Mix together in salad bowl the frozen peas, almonds, celery, onion and cauliflower florets.
Combine and add to pea mixture just enough to coat the sour cream, mayonnaise and salt and pepper.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef in 2-quart saucepan on medium heat.
Chop up tomatoes and add to ground beef.
Stir in tomato paste.
Add bag of mixed vegetables.
Add remaining seasonings.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat to low and let simmer 30 minutes.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together; roll into balls.
Press with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: texas salad(club member: clint hudson)
directions: Cut up bananas and sprinkle dry pudding over them. Drain fruit; cut into bite-size pieces. Add to the banana mixture. Add partially thawed strawberries; mix.
Refrigerate.

title: warm split-pea and carrot salad(low-fat)
directions: Rinse and drain peas.
Bring peas, water and salt to boil in medium saucepan; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 18 to 20 minutes or until peas are barely cooked. Stir in sprouts, carrots and bell pepper during final two minutes of cooking.
Drain mixture if necessary.

title: 6 flour tortillas
directions: Mix baking powder, salt and flour.
Cut in shortening.
Slowly add water.
Knead 5 minutes.
Shape into 6 balls.
Cover and let rise 15 minutes. Form balls into thin circles.
Place immediately into extremely hot skillet.
Flip when tortillas blister.
Keep wrapped in paper towel to keep warm.

title: hoppin' john soup
directions: In 8 quart Dutch oven, bring peas and water to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Stick cloves into ham hocks.
Add ham hocks, tomatoes, onions, bouillon cubes, bay leaves, garlic and pepper to peas.
Cover and simmer until peas are tender, about 1 hour.
Remove ham hocks.
Discard cloves.
Remove meat from hocks and add to soup.
Bring soup to a boil and stir in rice.
Reduce heat and simmer until rice is done.
Discard bay leaves.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Put sauerkraut in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix in sliced sausage.
Spread dressing on top.
Slice a tomato over that. Crumble several rye crackers on top of tomatoes and top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain.
Cook margarine, soup and water chestnuts on low heat for 10 minutes.
In casserole dish, place layer of broccoli soup mixture and half of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Put onion rings on top and let brown.

title: pineapple-ginger dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Yields 2 cups.

title: bloody mary's
directions: Boil first 6 ingredients 10 minutes and simmer.
Add tomato juice, water and vodka.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: chocolate cake dessert
directions: Crumble half of cake in a large serving container.
Prepare pudding according to package directions, using 1 1/2 cups milk per package (6 cups total).
Pour half of pudding over crumbled cake. Spread half of Cool Whip over pudding and sprinkle one crushed Heath bar on top of Cool Whip.
Repeat layers.
Yield: 15 to 20 servings.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: beer batter
directions: Mix all together and batter fish, chicken, etc.

title: autumn soup
directions: In 1-qt. saucepan melt margarine; add vegetables and saut over high heat, stirring frequently, until tender-crisp, about 1 minute.
Add water, squash, and broth mix and stir to combine; cook until mixture comes to a full boil.

Reduce heat to low, cover, and let simmer until squash is soft, about 15 minutes. Using a wooden spoon, press some of the squash against inside of saucepan to mash; stir in beans and bacon and let simmer until flavors blend, about 5 minutes longer.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Cut vegetables into bite size chunks.
Boil the chicken breasts until tender; remove.
In the same water (for added flavor), boil carrots and celery about 10 minutes.
Add broccoli. Cook until vegetables are just tender; drain.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: Mix moist with dry ingredients.
Grease and flour an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in square glass dish.
Freeze at least 4 hours.
Slice and serve.

title: traditional potato latkes
directions: Combine green onions, potatoes, flour, egg, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Heat 1 1/2 teaspoons oil in a medium nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Drop mixture by slightly rounded measuring tablespoonfuls into skillet, spreading level with back of spoon.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix together pumpkin, sugar and oil.
Add egg and beat well. Sift in dry ingredients.
Bake in a greased jelly roll pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
To make frosting:
beat the egg, confectionary sugar, margarine and vanilla until smooth.
Frost squares and sprinkle with chopped walnuts.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter together. Add eggs, buttermilk and coconut. Mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: pig in a basket
directions: Mix your favorite biscuit dough.
Wash and grease hands.
Fold a smoky link or hot dog in a few tablespoons of dough or about the amount you would use for a biscuit.
Bake until biscuit is almost done.
Remove from oven and put a slice of cheese on each one. Bake another 5 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and mix all ingredients except crackers.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: catalina chicken stir fry
directions: Heat dressing, soy sauce, and garlic powder in a large skillet.
Stir in chicken and cook completely, about 8 minutes. Add vegetables and cook.
Cook rice according to directions. Serve chicken over bed of rice.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Chill and serve.
This will have the same consistency of macaroni salad.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix according to box directions.
Add oleo, 1 egg and lemon juice well and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix rest of ingredients with mixer until smooth and spread over first mixture. Bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes.
Do not overbake!
Edges will be browned and set; middle will be barely set.
Cool before cutting into squares.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix well.
Very good for Sloppy Joes, chicken and pork.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Place uncooked rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix dry onion soup with boiling water.
Add mushroom and chicken soup (undiluted) to onion soup and water.
Pour 3/4 of this mixture over rice in baking pan.
Place chicken breasts on top; pour remaining soup mixture over chicken.
Bake in 325° oven; bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until chicken is tender and well cooked.

title: minted citrus carrots
directions: In a small bowl, whisk juices, mint and pepper together.
Toss with shredded carrots and refrigerate.
(Serve cold.)

title: yaki manju
directions: Beat
first
6 ingredients in mixer; combine with flour and baking
powder.
Refrigerate
for 30 minutes.
Form dough into 1 inch
balls;
flatten
it enough to cover "An".
Place "An"
balls in center of the flattened dough, pinching bottom together to seal it, and shaping them into cube, about 1 inch square.
On
a medium
hot
griddle, cook all six sides until lightly brown. Makes dainty little tea cakes.

title: german sweet pickles
directions: Soak whole cucumbers in salt water 7 days.
Take cukes out; wash (peel if desired) and slice.
Soak in alum water for 24 hours.
Be sure cukes are covered.
Take cukes out and wash 3 times in water.
Next, mix remaining ingredients.
(For lighter pickles, tie spices in cheesecloth.)
Bring vinegar, sugar and spices to a boil.
Pour over cukes.
Let set 4 days.
Pack in jars.
Bring pickling solution to a boil; pour over cukes and seal.

title: valentine puff pizza
directions: Unfold 1 sheet of puff pastry onto a lightly floured surface. Roll out to a 12-inch square.
With a sharp knife, trim 1 inch from each side.
Set strips aside.

title: date cookie
directions: Drop by teaspoon and bake in 350° oven.

title: bread noodle soup
directions: Mix by hand.
Put through meat grinder.
This makes the noodles.
Add to hot chicken broth.
Simmer gently 5 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix onion soup mix with rice in oblong dish.
Place chicken on top of rice mixture.
Thoroughly mix soup with 1 can of water and pour over chicken and rice.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300°.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Reserve 1 cup cake mix for topping (dry).
Combine cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Press in bottom of oblong pan lightly greased. Mix pumpkin, 2 eggs and evaporated milk together; pour on top of crust.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar, cinnamon and 1/4 cup butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over top of pumpkin.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cut in squares.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix oatmeal and buttermilk; let stand 1 hour.
Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together; add to the creamed mixture.
Mix in oatmeal mixture.
(Note:
Can add cut dates or jelly in each muffin at this point.)
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Can also be put in refrigerator and baked in the morning.

title: catalina french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar with a tight-fitting lid and shake.
This can also be mixed in a blender, although the color becomes creamier rather than translucent.
If preparing in a blender, mix all ingredients, except onion.
Stir in finely minced onion by hand.
Refrigerate.
Makes 2 cups.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger; add onion.
Put in large kettle and add tomato paste, kidney beans, chili powder, salt, tomato soup and water.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Makes a 5-quart ice cream pail full and it freezes well.
Good to take on camping trips or out to the fish house.

title: biscuits-even-i-can-make
directions: Heat oven at 450°.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together in a bowl.
Blend in sour cream.
Stir in milk to make a soft dough.
Put a small amount of flour on a board.
Turn dough out onto the board and knead gently for a few minutes. Shape dough into 1/2-inch biscuits.
Bake on lightly buttered baking sheet for 10 minutes or until lightly browned on top.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix flour with sugar.
Add well beaten eggs, buttermilk, oleo, vanilla and 2/3 of the coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cottage cheese-mushroom loaf *
directions: Saute onion in oil in large frying pan on medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add the chopped mushrooms and garlic and saute 10 minutes longer.
Stir the cottage cheese into the mushroom mixture.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix until well blended.
Spoon into a well-greased (spray) 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes or until set.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: jalapeno taco sauce(canned)
directions: Cook until tomatoes are done.
Can or freeze.
This is good ladled over cream cheese and served as a dip for corn chips.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend all well except bread. Cut off top of bread.
Scoop out insides.
Spoon dip into bread.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spray 12 muffin tins with Pam. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Add next four ingredients and mix well; put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with butterscotch morsels on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: five green salad
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, tear salad greens into bite sized pieces.

title: chocolate walnut drops
directions: Sift flour once; measure. Add baking soda and salt and sift together 3 times. Work butter with spoon until creamy. Add sugar gradually and cream together until light and fluffy. Add egg. Add chocolate and blend well. Add flour alternately with milk, a small amount at a time, beating until smooth after each addition. Add nutmeats and vanilla. Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 2 dozen drops.

title: banana date bread
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening. Add mashed bananas and lemon juice.
Add dry ingredients and dates. Grease and flour loaf pan. Add bread mixture and bake for 1 hour.
Test for doneness.

title: chocolate coconut cookies
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Add pudding and flour. Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for about 10 minutes.
Do not let brown.

title: easy one-dish ham bake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix soups, broccoli, 1 cup milk, the ham and onion powder in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix Bisquick and milk.
Pour evenly over soup mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.
Bake 30 to 33 minutes or until light golden brown.
Let stand at least 5 minutes before serving.
